New learner Circus Clowns        Once Upon A Circus, there was a clown. His name was Freddy. He needed to hire somebody cause his boss said that he needed another clown to intertain the kids on Saturday for the big Circus play. If he did hire somebody, all of the other clowns would have to teach the clown to do tricks and everything. That might take a while, so Freddy thought he needed to hire one almost right away.            So, Freddy took a walk down to the park. He took a glance at the park from around the corner. He didn't see anybody from around the corner, but he needed glasses because he had bad eyesight. So he walked farther, until he finally got there. Freddy saw two 2 year-olds, two 5 year-olds, three 13 year-olds, and 1, just one, 18 year-old. The perfect age to become a circus clown. Freddy thought. Even more perfect that there's only one. Fred let out some humour. (if you couldn't notice, sometimes Fred had a bad sense of humour. Fred is short for Freddy so you don't have to say FREDDY. As the other circus clowns said.)   'Hi, what's your name?' Fred went up to the girl that was 18.   'Hi, my name is Meg, do I know you?' The girl replied.   'No, I don't think so, but I was going to ask you something.'   'What was that sir?' Meg said.   'I was wondering if you would like to come work for me at the circus?'   'I would have to know what time and what days it would be on.'   'It would be the whole week. Some days you would be working for long hours but other days short hours.' Fred inquired.   'Yeah, I would be okay with that,' Meg said happily.   'Awesome! The one thing I would have to know from you is what your talent is, if that's okay with you.' Fred announced.   ' Oh, sure. My talent is that I LOVE gymnastics, and I go to practice in Iowa Falls. Crowds of people come to watch me do my fancy trick called THE SPIN. One time Taylor Swift came and watched me. It was the best day of my life!' Meg was excited talking about that.   'Sounds fun, do you want to go home and talk to your parents about it real fast?' Fred said.   'Yeah, be right back.' Meg replied.   'Okay,' Fred responded.            As soon as she got back, she said her parents said yes. Freddy was happy. Then they got to right back to the circus and practice.            Meg was so good at gymnastics that she mastered the new moves she had to learn in no time. Circus clowns were so proud of her and she did great at the big play!                 And all of the circus clowns lived happily ever after!!!!!

It's not easy living the life of a circus performer. You have to have lots of skill and talent to live in a circus. Even if your a kid you still go to bed about at twelve o'clock a.m. You have to give up absaloutly everything to become a circus preformer. We interviewed nine year old Loki about how she liked the circus life.        'It's fun but not the easiest job. And you might think you get to skip school because you joined the circus, but you still have to read, write, and do math in a one classroom trailer that comes with us where ever we go. I started doing gymnastics when I was five years old so I am rather good at being a trapize artist. My trick to not being scared even though i'm so high up is to just look at my mom on the other side. My whole family is in the circus but we do not all do the same thing. My brother, Tio, is an assintant clown. He gets to ride unicycles. My dad is the lion tamer. At dinner time we dont get to get to much because we are performing in a little while. We do ten shows a week so when the show is over I am very tired. The show goes to ten thirty p.m. and I go to bed at 12:00 a.m. In a couple of days we head to a different town. You may think it's exciting going from place to place but sometimes I wish that we could just settle in one spot that I can call home.'             As you can see it is not an easy life. You have to do many things to become a circus performer. With the crowd going wild and clapping their hands, you think it would be wonderfull, but ask yourself, do you think that you would want to swich lives with a circus performer?

Life in a Circus   By: Diego        April 11, 2013                    Things that happen in a circus is crazy like when people perform on tight ropes they have to walk on the rope trying not to fall of the rope. If they fall then everyone will laugh at the person who is doing that trick so that is just one thing and there are more tricks that are harder than that so it is hard. When people perform it is hard because they have to practice lots of times so they don't fail that is why when they do tricks they practice lots of times so they don't fail so practice makes perfect.                     My first reason that you should practice is that when you are on a balance beam you don't fall and get caught in the net when they fall off they get laughed at when they fall. Also when you fall off you might get injured when you mess up or maybe the net is to long and you still hit the ground a little hard. Some people that are on the balance beam they are sometimes blind and have a large stick that is about 10 or 15 or 20 feet long. They have to carry that all the way across the rope blinded. One person did that and fell on the rope which made him sit down on the rope and again he fell off this time. That is why you need to practice all the time so you can master it.                      My second reason is that when elephants go on bouncy balls they have to train them to stand on the balls and they train them to hold each other so they don't fall. They have to keep them skinny so that when they get on the balls the ball doesn't pop right when they are in the middle of doing their trick. The balls that they use to put the elephant on are strong so that when they get on the ball won't pop. The elephants hold on to each other because the elephants can't hold their balance they don't fall on their back or slip to their side. That is another reason why you should practice all the time.                      My Third reason why you should practice is that when clowns fold and twist balloons they have to practice folding and twisting the balloon. When people become clowns they practice before they go out and give kids balloon animals he has to know how to make them and how to do it without popping the balloon in the kids face. When clowns do tricks like the flower that shoots out water when you try to smell it they have to know where he should shoot it. If he shoots it anywhere then he might get the person in the eye. That is another reason why you should practice before you so your act on stage.                                                                                                                                                            Those are reasons why when you go to a circus and sign up for it then you have to practice all the time so that you won't fall or get hurt. Practicing make perfect because if you try to be a juggler them you have to learn how to juggle about five which should be a maximum amount of rings to juggle. So if you mess up them some people will laugh about how you failed or boo at you. That is why you should practice all the time when you try to join a circus.

In the Circus                                By Kallen Miller             Hi, I'm Anthony Kastellor. I live with a circus group called Magic Wonders Circus. I live all over the world, because we never stay in one place for long. I've been to all the continents, including Australia, my favorite one. I travel every week for 7 months and 14 days. I work from 5:00am to 11:00pm.                Here is a normal day at Magic Wonders Circus:            5:00am I wake, get dressed in uniform and head to pie car for breakfast. The crew at this time is setting up tents, lights, and music for todays show. I have time before school, so I normally go to see Giggles and Bunny-Hunn the clown. They let me play around with their bowling pins and trinkets. We usually, to get excersize, play tag.             8:00am I go to school with the other boys and girls. we learn everything that normal kids learn and how to do some circus acts. Many of us speak English, but all of us now every language there is. It helps us with our travels.              2:30pm School is over. Now we get a 30 minute break. I play with my friends, Ayessha and Herbert. We usually play games with the clowns for awhile. Then we just play our own.              3:00pm practicing and dishes. My daily activities. I am an acrobat. I practice on a trampoline and do tricks on horses. One time my mother fell off one and onto a trampoline. She was not hurt.             6:30pm It is now dinnertime. We don't eat alot before a show. We do 14 shows each week. 2 on each day.              10:30pm The show is over. I am sooooo pooped out! Usually we dont do very long shows. oh well.              11:00pm Good night.

Life at the Circus                               I nevously peaked behind the big, red, velvet curtains and listend the spectators cheering, hungry for action, as the ring master had a smart dog jump into a orange hoop. Worried that someone would see my face, (which was covered with bright makeup) looking at them, I quickly ducked back be hind the curtain. As soon as the audience gave one last cheer, I knew that I would have to go on. 'don't be scared, don't be scared, don't be sacared,' I told myself.                    I am Kathrine, and I spend my life at the circus. I work as a acrobat. Every week we have to preform. Every day, we have to practice. I had known I wanted to be in the circus when I was only about four years old. My family and I were at our very first circus together. A clown with a bright smile came up to me and handed me a polka dot flower. I smiled big too and laughed so hard. Then I saw the acrobats. I begged my parents to take gymnastics class. When they had heard enough of my whining and complaints, they finally let me.                    That is how I became an acrobat. I worked very hard, in fact a little too hard. I guess my legs were too straight, or my toes were too pointed, or I was too shakey. It was tough, but when I FINALLY got everything right, my toes were perfectly pointed, my legs were perfectly straight, and I was perfectly still, I was so proud. I congragulated myself and was hoping that that would be my start as a professinal acrobat.                     That was my start as a professional acrobat. Because of that now I am on posters and huge billboards with me spinning on thin ropes wearing sparkly and colorful costumes. And like I told you before, my face had bright makeup all over. 'Thats me!' I think every time we go past one. I fell in love with all this circus buisiness. Everytime it is my turn to be on stage, though I am nervous, I try my very best, and it is absolutly worth it. When I am backstage I always say to my self, 'What am I doing?!' But after, I always say, 'That's so fun, I want to go again!'                     As I carefully and gently walked on to stage, with the bright lights shining on my face, I wasn't scared anymore because I because I believed that I could really do it as long as I try my very best. Trying my very best is hard, but once again it is absolutly woth it. Being in the circus can be tough, but it is also very enjoyable. This is what life is like  at the circus.

When you first wake up you have to eat breakfast quick because you have to get ready for the morning show.  After you eat breakfast you have to practice for your act.  My act is training lions to jump through hoops.  Hopefully it's not your turn to pick up after the elephant.  After you practice it's time for lunch. all you get is some cheese burgers and fries.                                               Show Time        Before the show the ring master will let everyone know the acts that will be happening.  Once your on your on.  first everyone goes on at once and it's a big fiasco.  You have to make sure you don't bump into anyone or they'll be very mad.  You wait anxiously until it's your turn.  First the trapeze artist are up, then the acrobats, and finally it's your turn. it's hard being a lion tamer, especially when people are watching.                                                  After The Show            After the circus is over you have to clean up.  During the clean up time you literally have to clean up everything.  After you're done cleaning up it's dinner time. you get a big dinner.                                               The Fun Times                   When you're not working you're having fun. You may think the clowns are the most fun you're wrong.  The most fun is the trainers with their animals.  It's fun riding on the unicycles when the clowns aren't around throwing water balloons at you.  The most fun though is climbing the trapeze wire.  I also like swinging on the trapeze swing.                                               Conclusion                As you can see the circus is not all fun and games.  As you have learned  it's mostly work not play I hope you know this before you join the circus.  Even though I have fun some times  it's not allways fun.

Hello i'm Carla S Jean, and i am a circus performer in the 'Georgia world circus'.And in that cicus i am a clown.When most people hear the word clowns, the think of paint,makeup,balloons,red noses, and all of that.But what people don't know is that clowns really aren't scarry.Why would anyone be scared of us? We make cute balloon animals, honk our big red noses,dress up in colorful costumes,and talk in a weird voice.IT'S THE BEST JOB EVER!We get to travel the world entertaining every summer.We go to China,Brazil,France,Jamaica,Mexico,Canada, and so many more!         We have over 1,000 performers!We have elephants, monkeys, birds, and a whole lot more.My father is a knife thrower.Which means he gets to throw knifes every night in the summer at inocent people.(Well actually just one person, we call him Sojo) Everyone in our circus is really nice.Well... all except for stephan.        My typical circus day is...       rise at 6:30 AM, get dressed, then have breakfast which my dad get's up super early to make for me.Then I go rehearse with half of our circus for that nights show.We only rehearse with half because we don't need all of the circus in one tent.After that we have lunch.Lunch is always curly's decision.(He won't ket us decide).It's usually fried chicken or something like that.We have 2 hours of free time right after lunch.I'm 14 years old so I can walk around and don't need to ask.That's what i do for those 2 hours.After that i have my tutor teach me my math,scisnce,social studies,and literature.Finally we have dinner at 6:00 PM.That's always a suprise.I have a curfew of 9:00.Our show is always at 7:00 to 9:00.That is my day.        My life is the best life anyone could ever wish for!

Hey, the circus is a fun place, but it is a lot of work.  As the ringmaster, it is my job to make sure that people are doing what they are supposed to be doing.  I also have to help other performers make sure that can do their act.  The lion tamer probably has the hardest   job of any performer because the lion is very dangerous.      In my downtime, I like to help the other performers practice their acts as well as my own.  The juggler is one of the ones I don't help because he sometimes juggles flaming chainsaws!  The trapeze artist also is not someone Id like to help as she flips around and does twists and twirls.  I could seriously hurt myself !  As for my own act, well, that's what this story is about.      When I first joined the circus, I had no act.  The old ringmaster, my father, was about to retire and I never even thought about becoming ringmaster.  I decided to ' try out ' for a clown. Well that was a joke! (HAH HAH!!! Get it,  joke!) Anyway, the clown didn't work out as I  previously said. Next, I thought about being a tightrope walker. That also didn't work thanks to my little slip I had that left me in the hospital for 4 weeks.  After I got out of the hospital, my dad was retired and that meant a position as ringmaster was now open.  I knew it would be imposable for a rookie to get the position as ring master.      It actually wasn't me who got the position but my older brother! (Can you believe it after how hard I've worked! )  So, I got a little angry. Wait. I shouldn't a little angry. I was VERY ANGRY.  I was so angry that I quit the circus.       I know this story is about how I got my job but it didn't happen the first year. Months later, I got married to a beautiful woman. (a.k.a The Trapeze Artist).  After I explained what happened, she encouraged me to try again. So I did.  When I got back to the circus my brother wasn't there. I was happy yet confused at the same time.  The juggler told me he had been diagnosed with spinal stinosis ( did I mention he was a dwarf ?)  The whole circus went to visit him the next day at the hospital.  He was completely paralyzed from the waist down. It was all so sudden.  Moments later, a machine started to make a constant beep and doctors rushed is and asked us to leave. I knew what this meant.   We had go back to the circus and the I was automatically ringleader. Simple as that. But that's not the end of the story. That's just the beginning. A year later we went back to the hospital not because of my brother, but because of our new born child. We named him Dillon after my brother ( who had really died.)  Dillon became the youngest member of the circus. He could ride a unicycle at the age of 3 months. Amazing isn't it.  Sometimes he fell, sometimes I fell when tried to ride to unicycle which was not a great idea by the way.   Our lives felt complete.  We needed nothing else.  That's when the scary thing happened.  Dillon started to throw up constantly.  We were very worried. We took him to the doctors office to get him looked over. The doctor said he probably had a appendicitis and that we should take him over to get an x-ray. Indeed his appendix had ruptured. They had to operate immediately.  The operation was successful but Dillon couldn't ride his unicycle for many months.  We needed another act. Clowns, jugglers, lion tamers. What else did we need? Then I had it.  We need a strongman.   We bought plane tickets all the way to Africa to find some of the strongest people in the world.  Many came to preform but we knew we could only choose one.  One man could dead lift 600 pounds! There's one possibility right there.  Another could bench 800 pounds.  The choice was hard because they both could lift the some amount of weight. We went with the second guy.  He seemed really interested about being in the circus.  He almost exceeded his maximum limit before we had to stop him. We had no choice but to take him.    He filled out his passport to America and started to travel with us.  Great news was waiting for us when we arrived.  Dillon could almost ride his unicycle again.  We were so excited that we threw a party. Everyone came and brought Dillon something. He got a golden unicycle from the juggler.  At the time he was 2 years old and still better than me on a bike.  After the party we had our first show. The next week, the circus was packed with people Everyone had been practicing their acts for weeks and still felt nervous.  We started of with the lion tamer then my wife, them the juggler.  After that we had Dillon do his routine. the crowd went wild and everyone did good.  My act was not only as a ringleader, but as a father, a husband, and a brother.  This was my family. This was my place. This was my life.

Life in a Circus                                             Life in a cicus is very hard work. It involves dedication and skill to be in a circus.Anyone who thinks life in a circus is easy should probably think again.If you want to find out what it is like to be in the circus then read on.          Being in the circus involves a lot of hard work. You have school,chores,practice then a show! Then by twelve o clock you are just barely getting into bed.          Being in the circus does have good things and bad thing about it. For example you do a lot of tours. So that means traveling and you dont get to see your family as much as you would like to. I      Beep! Beep! Beep! Groaning, I slam down the off button of my alarm. I stretch, yawn, get dressed into my overalls and head over to the pie car for breakfast.           Oh! What am I thinking? I need to introduce myself! Hi, my name is Ariana Lasnier. I'm not your average 12 year old. I have spent most of my last 5 years touring the world with my family in the circus. I know what you're probably thinking... I'm a freak that can bend into a pretzel on a tightrope. Well, I'm not. Being in the circus is so much different than that. I'm part of the acrobats section. Not to brag, but we do A-MA-ZING tricks while hanging from ropes and so on. Anyways...          You get the point. Now, back to the story. On my way to the pie cart, I realize something. It's abnormally quiet. That's odd...  At the pie car, I sit down at a table and wait. And wait. And wait. Where is everyone? After what seemed like ages, Michelle, our cook arrives.    'Finally...' I mumble, my stomach growling.   'I'm sorry dear, I was in the back helping your mother. She's coughing up a storm!' Michelle apologizes, clanking the pans on the stove.   'W-what do you mean? I mean, she'll be okay for the show tonight won't she?' I ask worried.   'Your guess is as good as mine!' She laughs.         I fake a nervous laugh to cover my anxiety. We can't go on without her! We need her to tame the lion! After a while my eggs and bacon are ready.   'Eat up or you'll be late for school!' Michelle commands.         Well of course I can't go to just one school due to the moving for 7 months each year. Instead us younger performers get home schooled. My mom teaches, of course she would if she wasn't sick.         I rush over to the schooling car. Class has just started.   'So today- *cough cough*- we are going to revise evaluating expres- *cough cough* expressions! Goodness sakes! I'm sorry for the cough!'   My mom exclaims.     'Gee mom, you're really sick! You could rest. We'll just do tomorrows test so you don't have to talk.' I suggest.   'Well, I guess...' She says unsure.         So we take our test then read a book. Finally.... Class is over and I head to the stalls for some chores. All I have to do is feed and groom the horses and clean the stalls. After that I have to practice my routine and then I'm done until the show. This would be easy but my mom can't help. Great. So I decide to do the parts I can, by myself. Like flips, twirls on the rope and so on.         When I finally finish I head over to my moms parlor. There she is coughing and coughing and coughing!    ' You really are sick aren't you...' I say in a hushed voice.   She groans. I'll take that as a yes.   'Who's gonna take your place then?' I question   'Well, *cough* I think maybe we could postpone the show.'    'No! We can't! We are already booked for at least a show per day!' I exclaim. What are we going to do? I thought. Then, it came to me!   'Mom! I could tame the lion!' I say. I regret what came out of my mouth right away, that thing could kill me!   My mom thinks, coughs, groans and finally says 'I need to rest.'         As I head towards the door I think. I guess I could at least try to tame the lion. I just need to suck it up and learn. I turn back to my mother one last time. 'Mom, I'm going to tame the lion.' Then, I leave.         At the lion cage I find Simba- the lion- sleeping in the corner.   'Simba... Simba...' I coo. He growls. Ok. Where is the food?  I scan the room and stop. Over in the opposite corner is raw fish. Yuck!   I quietly shuffle over to the corner. I slowly stick my hand in the bucket. Of course being myself, I fully extend my arm in front of my face and hold it by the tail like a pair of dirty socks. I throw it to the lion. Out of nowhere it pounces over to the fish and rips it apart. Ok I can do this...         After about 2 or 3 hours, I'm finally done with my 'training'. Fingers crossed I don't die tonight. Time to get ready for the show!          I scurry over to the makeup parlor. All they do is powder my face a put on some mascara, lipstick and eyeshadow. Now, my costume is not exactly the most comfortable outfit on earth. It's a short dress with hanging, itchy fabric at my waist. Then, of course, is my tights. Now I look circus ready.         As I jog over to the main tent, I pass my biggest horror of the night. The lion being pushed, in its cage of course, over to the tent. Can you say death sentence? My head is spinning. This isn't right. I shouldn't be doing this, that lion will rip me apart! My knees feel weak. I feel dizzy. It's too much! Suddenly, everything goes black.         'Ariana...' The darkness calls.   'Ariana.' Closer, louder this time...   'Ariana!' Out of nowhere I'm snapped back into reality and being shaken by Joshua ( my acrobat partner). My eyes flutter open.   'Oh thank god your awake! We're on in 10 minutes!' He sighs of relief.   'W-what happened?' I mutter.   'I don't know. We found you passed out on the ground a few yards outside the entrance.' He explains.   'Is my mother okay? What about the lion?'    'She's still sick. But we have a substitute performer. Duh!' He laughs.   ' Sub-substitute!? I spent hours training with that lion!' I complain.   'Its fine... Anyways the audience came in and they-' he was cut of.   'It's show time!' My father exclaims in his announcer voice.         We take the ladder up to our ropes. Hanging there we wait for our signal. The lights go out.   'Ladies and gentleman... Welcome, to the Balabam Circus. Pleeeaaaassseeee, put your hands together for our first act of the night, the acrobats!' The announcers voice booms over the loud speakers.   The audience cheers.          I look down at the dirt floor far below us. I take a deep breath and let go of my rope. Swinging by the the rope attached to my feet I twirl over to Joshua who grabbed my arms and flipped us both. Slowly we put our arms out to show my rope is unattached and we are both just hanging by his rope, and we are only attached by a chain in our mouths. I open my mouth to release the chain. The sensation of dropping washes over me, only to be stopped by the swinging bar a hook onto. The crowd goes wild. Around me I see all the girls hanging by silk, twirling endlessly with so much grace. I pull up to position myself to sit on the swing. Only to leap through the air while Joshua swings on his swing to catch me. Again the crowd goes bonkers.          After a moment of them cheering I jump and plunge through the air, flipping over and over again. After a few seconds I blindly spin around. Trying to aim towards the landing mat. I realize I'm off by a foot or two and won't make it to the mat. Suddenly, something slams into me from behind. Joshua. He Had noticed my mistake and altered his path to help me.          I tumble onto the mat trying not to look dazed. And stand with my toes pointed and arms out. The crowd claps and we exit to the back section.         The crowd becomes muffled as a sit backstage.    'Hey uh, thanks for helping me out.' I mutter awkwardly.   'No problem. Hey wanna go get some popcorn?' He asks   'Sure!' I say relieved to get away from the quiet room.         After an hour and a half or so we get ready for our final bow. Oh duh! My mom! She came out and helped with the lion. Anyways, at the final bow I notice someone. Danielle Stone. My heart leaps up my throat. She waved her hand for me to come over after the bow.         I scurry over to her after explaining to my dad a friend was here. Danielle is, well was, my best friend before I started the circus.    'Oh my god! Hi! I haven't seen you in ages!' I shout over the noise hugging her.   'I know! You did awesome! So, how you been?what are you up to?' She smiles.   'Oh nothing. Just, you know, touring the world and such...' I joke.   ' Well about that... I'm joining the circus!Im going to be an acrobat like you!' She exclaims throwing her arms up.   'Really that's great! Well, as much as I'd love to talk I have to go. See you soon.' I hug her once more and walk away. Time for the meeting. I head to the back of the tent         Joshua waves me over to sit by him at our performance meeting. I blush and sit down. I mean, he is kind of cute... Moving on! The meeting is basically reviewing how we did and stuff. While they talk I rest my head on my arm. Although there we some bumps, today was a pretty great day!

The Great Circus!                   This is a story of how I, Isabell Castini, got in the circus! It started out one summer morning. I was getting ready to go to the park when suddenly my dad says, 'Isabell. Do you want to go to the circus instead?' I called back, 'Sure!' So I got ready to go to the circus! I was in the car when my dad asked me, 'Isabell, what would you be if you were in the circus?' I replied, 'Well, I guess I would be an acrobat!' My dad kept driving and said,'Well, Isabell, how about I get you lessons to be an acrobat? This is the perfect age to start!' He says that because im about 11 years old so he wants me to learn how to be something I want to be.                      We got to the circus at exactly 12:00 o'clock. We were just in time! The first act was clowns! I watched the clowns as they happily threw pie in each other's faces! It was so funny! The next act was the acrobats! I was so excited! They did flips and twirls and whirls! I was so amazed! Then after the show was over I told my dad, 'Yes. I would love to take acrobat lessons!' So the next day my dad called the city's office. 'Hello? Do you have any gymnastic lessons or acrobat lessons? I am not sure what they are called.' Asked my dad. 'Yes, all you have to pay is $20 a month.' said the phone lady. 'Okay. When do the next lessons start?' asked my dad. 'Next Tuesday? Okay we will be there!' 'Well?' I asked. 'You may come next Tuesday ok? Do NOT let me forget! This is very important!'                   A week had passed and my dad woke me up super early! 'The early worm catches the bird!' My dad cheerfully said. 'Um...dad? Isn't it supposed to be the early bird catches the worm?' 'Oh. Right.' said my dad as he laughs. 'Well anyways. Today is the day!' 'What?' I asked while yawning. 'You are supposed to go to your lessons!' my dad replied. 'At 7:00 in the MORNING?' I asked. 'No!' my dad says, 'You are supposed to be getting up early if you want to be in the circus like your big sister.' 'Okay. I will try to be more responsible.' I replied.                  Finally after what had seemed like an hour to me (which had only been about thirty minutes.) we were there! I entered the building and the counter lady was standing right there like she had been waiting for me. I asked her what time it was so I would know that she wasn't some kind if robot or something. She said it was 8:00 A.M. 'Okay, so maybe it was an hour.' I said to myself. 'Go right in there.' said the counter lady. As I went inside I saw girls who were probably up since 5:00 in the morning doing flips and really cool tricks! 'Wow! I wish I could do that!' I said out loud. Then a lady came up to me and said, 'Hello there, My name is Mrs. Belini. Are you one of our newcomers?' 'Um, yes.' I replied shyly. 'It's fine we are all family here! you don't need to be shy.' she said. she led me to a balance beam and held my hand. She told me to climb up the balance beam. It wasn't very high and she said she would hold my hand so I climbed up on the balance beam. She told me to try to jump off and spin 360 degrees. So I jumped off and tried to spin and I did! She said that was beginner stuff. I was so happy that I got off to a good start!                  A couple of years passed and I was doing AWESOME! I was now 15 and I knew a ton of stuff about the circus and the Belini Brothers! I was thinking about joining them. Then I knew something was going on. My circus/gymnastics teacher's name was Mrs. Belini! She is their SISTER?! I ran to my dad and told him, and he said he already knew. 'Isabell, she is going to try and get you into Belini Brothers!' screamed my dad. 'What?! I barely know anything about circuses and-,' my dad cut me off. 'It's fine! Do you think that she just wants to do that just because?' 'No.' I replied quietly. 'Then you are fine. She told me that you will be able to see them on Friday. Ok?' my dad told me. I started to stutter, 'Um, but, when? How? Whe-' 'Stop stuttering. you will be fine.'                 A week passed and I was ready! I got up REALLY early and my dad wasn't even up yet. I took a shower and got dressed, and I sat in the living room waiting for my toaster waffle to be done. My dad walked in the room thinking nobody was up yet. He almost screamed, 'INTRUDER! INTRUDER!' 'I woke up early dad just like youi said. Right?' He started to laugh. 'Ok what is the big occasion?' he asked. I gasped. 'You mean you don't remember?! The Belini Brothers? We are going there, remember? So i can audition?' 'Oh yeah!' He yelled. 'Hurry! Get dressed! Take a shower!' 'It's ok dad I already did all that.' 'Ok.' he said.  3 hours had passed and finally we got to the car and started driving.                 We finally got there and one of the Belini brothers told me to go on the stage and audition. I was so scared I could barely feel my feet! So I got on the balance beam and did a bunch of cool trips and flips. Mrs. Belini also taught me how to do the acrobat tricks in the air. I climbed the ladder. Everything looked so small but I saw my dad and Mrs. Belini Cheering me on. So I jumped and did one flip. I grabbed the bar and did flips. I was so amazed that I could do all this stuff! Then the Belini Brothers spoke. 'Isabell Castini!' I thought they were going to kick me out but they just started to laugh and dance. 'We want YOU to be in our circus!' I panicked and screamed, 'AHHHH! I am so happy!' My dad told me 'CONGRATULATIONS!' I packed my things up and said, 'Thank you dad.' I got on the train and left. And that is the story of how I got into the circus!                                                                             The End

In the Circus           Welcome to the morning of the Circus. My name is Kenzi, I am   an acrobat in the Circus.   I don't always work alone. I have a partner and her name is   Morgan,she is a really good acrobat. Morgan is a really good partner,she is very kind. She will brighten up your day no mater what.   We have a very busy schedule.       7:30- We wake up at seven thirty and go get breakfast at the Eat and Meet bus.       8:00-At eight we go back to our bus and get dressed in our warmup clothes.       8:30- We go to our stations, there are about five stations, our station is acrobats.We practice all sorts of flips.       10:15- We go to the harness to practice acrobats in the air.       11:30- At eleven thirty we eat lunch at the Eat and Meet bus.       12:45- When we are back at the bus we get to just relax and take naps or play with the animals.       2:15- At two fifteen we practice acrobats in the air and acrobats on the ground for the last time before the show.       4:15- When we are all done we go back to are buses and take showers and do our hair.       5:30-At five thirty we go to the circus tent and watch the finale touches being made.       6:00- Then finale the doors open people take their seats and we get started.       8:30- The circus is over we had a wonderful day.           We do the same routine almost every week. Also we have a   show almost everyday.I do miss going home to my family and friends,  but over all I LOVE the CIRCUS!!!

Some people think life is easy in the circus. I, Rachel Tatley,   know better. I'm an acrobat in the circus, and believe me, it's not as easy as you think. We have to wake up very early in the morning to do our jobs, and we go to sleep very late. We do several shows in over 150 different cities in a year! I travel with my family, and all the circus performers live in one big trailer. My mother is an animal trainer, and my father is a clown.                 Even though we live in a trailer, we still go to school. The   school just travels with us. Believe it or not, our school is just like yours! We have our regular lessons, along with tests. We also use computers. But because circus performers come from all over the world, a lot of my classmates speak different languages. I have always wanted to play an instrument or do a sport, but we never have enough free time to do other things.                  When school is over, we have do to chores and practice our circus tricks. Being an actrobat takes a lot of agility and perseverance. I took gymnastics when I was smaller, so I know how to do a lot of the flips and other things in the job of being a circus performer. In the circus, I still have a lot of friends even though we're not in our real home. We try to adapt to different temperatures, but it's hard because we move around so much.                   Sometimes life is hard for us circus performers, but I know I will always enjoy being an acrobat in the circus.

The Amazing Bella   By Isabella Woodhouse             Hello my name is Bella and I have story to tell you about my experience in the circus. It all started on May 4, 2010, my birthday, I was at my car getting ready for the next trip to Nevada. Then all of a sudden my car started moving. I looked out the window and to my relief we were just leaving early, but noticed my cat was gone. My cat was sitting on top of another car. I hit the emergency button that made all the cars stop,'Screeeech!' I grabbed my cat and we were off again. I thought all the crazy stuff was all done for the day, but I was wrong, very wrong.             Finally we stopped in Nevada for the week and we started to set up for the night. Then suddenly I heard a,'BOOOOMMM' I shot out of my car and ran to the tent. I looked around and saw that part of the stands were lose and fell of. I grabbed a wrench and ran to the stands and started tightening the loose screws. I guess I set an example because then everyone in the circus pitch in. Like I said before there was more in store for me that day.             The show started in ten minutes and everyone was filling the stands. I used to be nevous, but I've been doing this for a while so I was exited. Especially since I learned a new tightrope dance. The show has begun, but something was wrong I could feel it. 'ROOAARR!' everyone screamed in terror. Luckily I learned how to tame a lion in circus school. I finally got the lion back in it's cage and everything was fine. The show was canceled that night,but that is fine because it was a wild day anyway.               Wow what a day. This was probaly the weirdest, wildest,and most wonderful birthday ever.

The Cheetah and the Stage Manager                 When many people weren't coming to the circus, the acrobats   decided getting a new animal might work. They decided to go and find and animal. The problem was that the circus had every animal known to be in the circus. They didn't know what to do. They went to Australia to find a kangaroo. The problem was the kangaroo just kept trying to hop away. Another problem was that the next performance was three days away. This was going to be their biggest crowd yet because they had advertised saying they had a new animal.                  The crew decided to go to Africa to find an animal. With one day left. When they brought the cheetah back from Africa, he wouldn't listen to anyone. Every performer tried to tame the cheetah.   During dinner time, our stage manager said that maybe he should try taming the cheetah. He hadn't tamed any animals before but we decided we should let him try. The cheetah was going to our grand finally. When we looked through the curtains, we saw that the crowd was huge. As usual, all the performers and the animals went. Then, it was the cheetah's turn.                   When the cheetah and the stage manager went into the place where the performers perform, everybody was cheering. All of us were peaking through the curtain trying to look. The cheetah was amazing. It jumped through flaming hoops, and walked on three legs. It was the best animal we trained ever. After the spectacular performance, we decided to let the stage manager also be the cheetah trainer.                                                         The End

Monique was devastating. I had known that she would never be the best in our circus, but I never knew that she truly had no talent. Already a half of the crowd was shouting angrily to Manny, our ringleader, and Monique. Shocked by the audience's response to her part in the show, Monique fled the stage and burst into tears as she ran to her trailer. I couldn't blame her for the audience's reaction. Many times the audience quality changed. In Atlanta, there were many happy people while in Salem, there were many grumpy people. Although most of the angry responses were because of the audience quality, I knew that part of it was because of her act.               Dandrum Circus was a very successful circus until Pansy Lynn quit. Pansy was about the best horseback rider in history. She was the one who wowed the crowd with her amazing horse tricks. To the public, she was known as 'Pansy the Horse Whisperer.' Sometimes Pansy would go to the audience and answer their questions and sign autographs. She loved the publicity. And her horse, Kay. Pansy loved that horse. He was proud, handsome, and Pansy would die for him. Actually, he died first.               Pansy cried her eyes out the day that the doctors declared Kay dead after he died of a disease. At first she refused to work with any other horse and stayed inside her trailer for weeks. Manny talked to Pansy and even sent her to a therapist to help settle her feelings. Pansy came back fresh and happy. It seemed like she had forgotten about Kay. I followed her to the stable when she was picking out a horse to practice with. I saw her come towards a beautiful tan horse like Kay, except it wasn't. 'You look so beautiful,' Pansy said as she stroked his mane,'like Kay.' She paused, making a shocked and puzzeled face. 'Where is Kay?' she said to herself. As if remembering, she sadly walked back to her trailer.                The next day, I heard that she quit. Jose, the circus manager, looked as red as a beet when he came out of the office trailer after his talk with Pansy. I didn't have a glimpse of Pansy that day and never saw her ever since.                We moved to Seattle. I helped post flyers for job openings in our circus. One of the jobs was Pansy's part with horses. Jose sat in his office interviewing many people who wanted a job. I had peeked through the window and had seen Jose's tired face after the interviews were done. It was after dinner and he was about to flip the sign that said 'Interviews in Session' to 'No Interviews' until a teenage girl with purple hair and bright blue eyes ran up to Jose. 'Are the interviews done already?' she asked. Jose looked around. No one else was in line. 'I guess one more is fine,' he said. When both of them went inside the trailer, I slipped back to my own trailer and had a good night sleep.                She got Pansy's part. Jose introduced her to everyone in the circus while we were eating breakfast. 'Her name is Monique and she claims that she is the 'horse whisperer' of this town.' We all clapped. At practice that day, I saw that she was not very good, but I didn't let that worry me. At least until showtime.                Monique ruined her part. She drove the horses too close to each other so that they were practically hitting each other. Then she fell off the horses and tripped herself and got herself stuck in the hay while the horses were chewing her hair. At least there was my part.                After Monique were my friends and me. We're called the 'Birds of the Trapeze.' I jumped and Ellen swang towards me. We caught eachother and danced around our course. Maylee and Lucy joined us. The crowd loved us. Now it was time for the finale. We all grabbed ropes that were in a circle and were somersaulting and changing spots. I've seen YouTube videos of us, and we were really good. Then Aimee jumped in the middle and we became tropical birds in paradise. We landed perfectly on our posts and posed. The crowd cheered wildly and we took a bow. They seemed to forget Monique.                Later that day, Manny told us that we saved the show. Monique had quit. 'If we find another bad performer, I'm not gonna put horse tricks on the show,' he said. We only had a day in Seattle. I wasn't sure he was going to find a replacement. That is, until I saw the long line of people outside the office trailer.

The circus kayos.                                                                                   Once, there was a circus performer named Chicken Yumyum.  She was a person who was not afraid of any type of snake, so she decided to join the circus.  Back then, people use to dance with constrictors in the circus.  It was all her talent.  So she decided to join the circus.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        She was entered in a circus in Tokyo.  There was many trains to pull stuff with help of trucks and ships.  Chicken was the last performer.  Her job was to stand on the horse while sprinting and dance with mean constrictor about 7 feet long.  It was a success!  She then went to Florida to do a huge practice.                                                                                                                                                                                                        While practicing Chicken thought she was going to be the best and most wealthy performer in the world.  However on the newspaper it said that a clown called the floating spirit could juggle on a very thin rope while bouncing on a ball with a monster unicycle.  Chicken got mad and said to herself,'that clown should try a constrictor till he falls of his rope and dies.'She practiced more and more and was going to preform much more better than the last one.  This time she was going to a lot better than her last preform.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     There were a lot more trains and ships and trucks.  Again she was last which was good.  The Floating Spirit was there that time.  He was on a rope that almost looked like a spider web with a unicycle and a ball while juggling 6 balls.  This time in his preferment he said,'THROW THE RATTLESNAKE.'Someone shot a rattlesnake in the air and he started dancing with it in one hand while the other hand was juggling the balls!  Chicken saw that the rattlesnake was weird and how he juggled and how he unicycles was weird.  Chicken didn't know how to juggle, but she did know she was not afraid of snakes.  She asked somebody who was in charge of the circus materials,'where are the rattlesnakes?'We don't have any rattlesnakes,'said the guy,'but we have corral snakes.'Chicken was confused, but she didn't care that much.  This time she got a 8 and a half constrictor with 2 corral snakes.  She put a unicycle on a horse that was much faster than the other horse.  She was a great success but more people cheered for The Floating Spirit than Chicken.  They through money and roses at The Floating Spirit.                                                                                                                                                                             All night Chicken thought about all the strange things that happened that night.  Then it hit Chicken that the clown was a fake!  There were strings on  the balls and on the clown!  He was also attached to the unicycle!  And there was no rattlesnakes in the circus and the rattlesnake was fake or dead because it never moved! 'Nobody would believe me,'she thought,'but he can ruin my career!'She was doing nothing for 5 minutes and then she had brilliant idea.  She dressed like an untalented person and asked somebody,'when and where is The Floating Spirit's next preferment?'The guy replied.' America, Main, Tuesday April 21, 9:30 pm.'That is where and when Chicken left.                                                                                                                                                                Chicken borrowed a spot light and went into the tent.  While 'The Great Floating spirit' was doing his fake moves Chicken aimed the spot light above the clowns head and turned it on.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       It showed the lines above his head and then everybody started shouting BOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOOO! and started shouting CHICKEN YUMYUM!                                                                                                                                                                       In conclusion, Chicken Yumyum died after a corral snake bit her and fell of a tight rope and was constricted by an anaconda about 16 feet long.  However, she was the most famous circus performer in history.

As you can see, being in a circus is hard, but fun at the same time. And I always want keep on doing it.

The Missing Circus Horse         'The worst possible event happened!' screamed Laura running into her trailer and throwing herself into her Moma's arms.  'What happened?' Moma asked. 'Papa's favorite horse, Lust, is missing!' Laura cried. 'Oh! That's just terrible! There is no show without Lust. He's the star of our circus you know.' Mama said, pulling Laura close. Suddenly, one of the circus clowns burst into  the trailer. 'The show is about to start Mrs. Cinders. We're all waiting on you.' the clown spoke in a goofy voice. 'Have you no idea that Lust is missing!' Moma practicly screamed.     'Lust is missing!' the clown said, his eyes bulging. ' That's right, and we're not doing the show without him.' Laura snapped. 'I don't know Laura. Not doing the show means losing a lot of money.' Moma said shaking her head. ' What are we waiting for then? On with the show!' the clown smiled, and waddled out of the trailer. 'Sorry sweetie.' Moma sighed as she walked out of the trailer and closed the door behind her.     'Don't worry Lust. I'll find you.' Laura exclaimed confidently. With that said, she grabed her flash light and snuck out of the trailer. The moment she got out she heard rustling in he underbrush. Instinctively she filcked on her flash light and pointed it tward the underbrush.All of a sudden, somebody put a hand over Laura's mouth and draged her into the prickly bushes.     Laura looked up and saw that it was her dad and Lust. 'Papa aren't you suppost to be at the circus, and how did you find Lust?' Laura asked. ' The circus life is so busy that I decided to run away with Lust.' Papa frowned. 'Papa, you could have just told us and we could have stopped our tour. Nobody would mind. All we want is for you to be happy.' Laura said, and hugged her dad. 'Really?' Papa asked. 'Really.' Laura said. With that said, Papa grabbed Lust's reins, took Laura's hand, and walked back to the circus.

The ringmaster has just introduced the dancing elephants. Good. I have seven more acts before my own. I do the math in my head. That leaves 84 minutes before my performance. Eighty-four minutes before I have to step out in front of the thousand-member audience. This is my first performance in front of an audience and yet I am performing the closing act.               My name is Anastasia Ludovic, but I am known simply by my stage name, Minnie. I am a flame swallower and a lion tamer. Since both my parents are acrobats, I was taught circus skills from a young age. I developed an interest in flame swallowing when I was nine-years old. My parents were reluctant to allow me to practice this act, but now, seven years later, I am a professional flame swallower and lion tamer. I learned how to swallow flame while standing upon a running lion's  back. But I had never done this in front of an audience. And, I get stage fright!               But it is too late now. I hear the ringmaster call out my name. 'Now presenting MINNIE!' he yells. I take a deep breath and step out onto the stage.         Twenty Minutes Later        My act has finished. The crowd is cheering louder than a lion' s roar. 'Encore!' they shout. 'Bravo!' I bow and then after several moments more of cheering, I go backstage where the rest of the crew piles on top of me in a big bear hug. I have never been happier.

Hi my name is Jessica, I'm 12 years old and my whole family's in the circus and we're all acrobats. Most people think that our life is just fun and no school, no homework just traveling and games in the circus, but no that's nothing like my life at all. I still have a normal life even if I am in the circus.       First of all, I do have school there are other kids on the circus train with me and we have one teacher. between circus acts we have school and homework. Even though I do live on a train I still have lots of responsibility, including taking care of my dog Fluffy and doing my chores.       The circus takes a lot of work including practicing for 8 hours everyday.I have to stretch a lot especially since I'm an acrobat we're the most flexible in the circus. I almost never get any sleep for example, one time we had a circus that went all the way from 4:00 to 11:55 P.M. and I didn't get to bed until 3:00 A.M. How The Circus Life of Jonny Burrito Started                         Hi, I'm Jonny Burrito and I will explain to you about how my circus life started.                         It all started 27 years ago in a small village called Burritoville. There were circus auditions to join the renown travelling circus called The Burrito Brothers. At the time I was only 7 years old. No person has ever made it into The Burrito Brothers at my age. My special talent was that I could walk on a tightrope.                        I was number 54 to audition. I nervously watched as people were being denied into The Burrito Brothers. My friend Barney was doing an acrobatic performance when he fell of the rope that he was holding on to and came crashing to the ground. He went into a coma.   That injury made me even more nervous.                        34,35,36,37,38,......54.                                     It was my turn. I did not want to go into a coma and i did not want to be denied. I wanted to be the youngest person to ever join The Burrito Brothers. The problem was that The Burrito Brothers did not want very young people to join their circus.                         'Well, are you coming or not 54?' Yelled the director.                          'Y-yes sir.' I stammered.                             As I climbed on to the tightrope I suddenly got butterflies in my stomach as I thought about poor Barney who went into a coma. I put my right foot on the rope and then my left foot and so on.                              I had 3 more steps...2......1.... I made it!!!!! All of the judges were clapping. The director announced, 'Congrats, Jonny. You are the youngest person to ever join The Burrito Brothers!!                                     That was how my career started.

Anyone who thinks circus life is nonstop play is crazy!I,Bella know different now. i live in a big trailer with my family. we travel 20,000 miles in 7 months each year,visiting 150 cities. i work from sunup to sundown. heres a typical day for me                7:00 AM i wake up,get dressed and go to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. the crews are setting up tents,lights, and music for tonight's show.                  9:00AM school time. our one room classroom schoolhouse travels with us. like any school ours has computers, tests and report cards. because the circus preformers are from all over the world, many of my classmates speak italian,french and other languages like my othr family. as we travel around the country, our geography lessons come alive.                   3:30 PM chores and practice i feed,water and groom the horses we use in our horseback acts.           Today, my dad practices somersaulting off a riding horse. im working on leaping on to a horse's back. It takes balance and concentration. Other kids are practicing jubbling or acrobatics. Our neibor walks baby leapords on a leash. Trainers are working with elephants, lions, and chimpanzees.                      6:30 PM Dinnertime! My family and I go to the pie car to eat, but we dont have much time because were preforming tonight. we do 10 shows a week. one each weekday, and a matinee on Wednesday, two on saturday and two on sunday.                 the show is over. Im wiped out. Walking back o our trailer, we passed the circus offices, concession stands, stables, and trailers. two days from now, we will be all set up in another town.                        12:00 AM in bed. Im thinking about the end of our touring season. It will be nice to go back to our real home in Florida. When I grow up, will I stand infront of an audience as a circus peformer like my parents? who knows ? The circus is fun, but its a busy and tough life.

Hi my name is jack me and my family are in a circus. It is very cool but it has some downfalls.   Some good parts are that you get to do some cool stuff. The bad parts are you don't get see friends or family.

I woke up at the sound of my alarm clcok at 7:00 A.M. I got up and picked out my normal clothing. I changed from my pajamas to my day clothes and went into the pie car for breakfast. I finish my breakfast and rush to the bathroom and brush my teeth. I go and watch the crew set up the tents, lights, and music for tonights show.       'Melanie, shouldn't you be getting ready for school?', Tony, a crew member asks me. I look at the time, and see that it's 8:30.           'Woops! Thanks Tony.', I say rushing to my room and start brushing my hair.       30 Minutes later, it's 9:00 A.M. I rush out of my room getting ready for school. You see our one-room schoolhouse travels with us. Like any normal school, ours has computers, report cards, and tests. Many of my classmates speak languages such as: French, Russian, and Italian. This is because in the circus life, you travel all around the world. As we travel the world, it's like our geography lessons come to life.        Once school is over, at 3:00 P.M. it's a quick break for me. The clowns let me play with their unicycles and juggling balls. I also play with my tiny dog, Noodle. Our trailer is to large for a small pet. I wish I could join after school activities (soccer, football, cheerleading, etc.) But we never stay in one place long enough.         At 3:30 p.m. It's chores and practice. I feed, water, and groom the horses. Tody my dad is practicing somersaulting off a horse. I'm practing spinning off a rope 300 ft. in the air. Everyone says I had guts to agree with doing that trick. (This trick was being postponed until two days from now.) Trainers are working with elephants, lions, and chimpanzees. Our neighbor walks baby cheetas on a leash. Other kids my age are practicing juggling and acrobatics.          6:30 P.M is dinner time! My family and I go to the pie car to eat. We don't eat much because we have shows every night after dinner. We do 10 shows a week. We have one each weekday; plus a matinee on Wednesday, two on Sunday, and two on Saturday.           10:30 P.M. The show is over. I'm tired and need some sleep. In two days from now we'll be in another country. I was hoping we'd go to Las Vegas, in Nevada. But I highly doubt that'll ever happen. I hopped under my covers and drifted to sleep. That night I had a strange dream about my spinning on a rope 300 ft. in the air, trick.                                                    THE DREAM        My palms were sweaty and I turned to face all the people counting on me, to do this trick. My hands gripped the rope. I climbed the rope, to the top and I felt the rope begin to spin. I gripped the rope even tighter with my sweaty hands. I plastered a fake smile on my face to cover up the fright. I saw the crowd cheering me on and my parents, the crew, and the other performers cheering me on aswell. Without thinking one of my hands let go of the rope. My smile was swept off when this happened. The crowds cheers got louder but everyone elses stopped. Everyone but the crowd had nervousness on their faces. I tried to put my hand back on the rope but the rope was spinning to fast. I finally got a grip of the rope with my other hand. I took a deep breath and my palms got sweaty again. I looked down, and that was the moment I realized I was afraid of heights. My breathes were quicker and my heart literally stopped. My hands slipped on the rope and when as I was falling I heard gasps and 'oh no's!' from the audience. The crew, my family, and other performers rushed to the rope. I closed my eyes tight and was waiting for impact. I slammed onto the floor, with a 'THUNK!' then I  blacked out.                                                 REALITY   I woke up sweating. I saw that my family was surounding me. They all looked worried, I noticed that I was crying. I wiped the tears off my cheeks and rubbed my eyes.        'What happened?', I asked, looking up to my family.          'You were crying and sweating. You were screaming in your sleep.', my sister, Alyssa, said still with a worried look on her face, 'What were you dreaming about?'          'I was dreaming about the rope trick. I was dreaming I fell off and I slammed into the floor.', I said, laying back down.           It was Saturday and my family gave me 'It's going to be okay, nothing will happens' before leaving the bedroom. I rubbed my eyes and got out of bed and headed to the pie car. I ate breakfast and went to go look at the rope.       I looked up at the rope and took a deep breath. I climbed the rope up to 300 ft. I looked down and it wasn't so scary.                            ON MONDAY AT THE SHOW           I looked at the people counting on me. This wasn't a dream at all. I sighed and climbed up the rope. I looked down and felt the rope begin to spin. I gripped the rope tighter and felt goosebumps go up my arms. I didn't realize my eyes were closed until I opened them and the crowd was cheering. I did it. I acomplished this trick nobody else would do. Im proud  of myself.

Big change               'Moooooooo.' I grew up on my grandmas farm with cows, pigs, chickens, horses, and cats. Her farm was blue and she had a gray silow about 15 ft. tall next to it. She lived in a big yellow house with a nice big porch for summer days. Being on the farm isn't easy, their are lot and lots of chores to do and you still have to go to school all at the same time. I live alone with my grandma because my parents didn't love me or want me so my grandparents took me in and two days after I got there my grandpa died of a heart attack.                Sometimes when I would have to feed the chickens, I would really swing around on the rope, and do cool acrobatics. I loved doing that kind of stuff, it would cheer me up and remind me of my dream to be in the circus.               One day when I was in my room at 6:30 right before I had to feed the chickens, I heard on the radio from my grandmas room that there was an open auditon to be in the circus. I wrote down all of the information I needed and thought of a plan to get there. My grandma doesn't like the circus, so my plan was to say I was going to just watch, when I would really tryout. I practiced my flips and tricks over and over again till they were perfect.              Finally it was the day, the day of the circus auditions. I asked my grandma if I could go and I was right my plan worked! When I got there, so many people were there I couldn't believe it! My turn was up, I was about to burst into tears and run off stage but I kept my cool.             'Ana dear, the phone is for you and I will allow it since well, you can find out for your self.'             'Coming, and o...k?'             I came to the phone and figured out why my grandma said what she did, I won! Out of 3,789 people, they liked me the best! We packed my stuff because I have to move in with the circus I can't just live at home. For my last day with grandma she didn't make me do any chores, the whole day was just fun and games on the farm. I am really going to miss my grandma, she was the only one who ever cared for me and that really means a lot.             It's my first day at the circus and boy what a busy day I have. First at 7:00 A.M. I have to get up and eat in the pie car (food truck for circus people). Then at 9:00 A.M. I go to school, just because I am in the circus doesn't mean I get to skip school. Inbetween 3:00 P.M. and 3:30 P.M. I get to have a break and play arouond with the circus acts and my friends from school. After that when it is 3:30 P.M. I have to practice my act and do chores. Right before the show I eat dinner in the pie car but not much because we have a show after. When my show is over I am wiped out and ready to go to bed. Finally at 12:00 P.M. I get to go to the trailer and plop down on the bed to fall asleep.            The circus is my dream but I miss my grandma more that anything. Life is really hard without anyone to take care of you and love you. I can't wait for the end of our touring season so I can go home to my grandma and spend time with her.

?A Day at the Circus       'Hello! I am a circus performer who works with horses. Here is a story about the average day at the circus       I wake up today in Tennessee. We traveled there after yesterday's performance. I get dressed and go over to the pie car for my breakfast.We're having bacon and pancakes, which is good, because I like pancakes.       Once we all get our fill, we have to set up the stage with lights and equipment. Then, we work on our training while the kids go to their small-sized school. We also have to take care of the elephants, horses, and all the other animals, along with making sure the equipment is clean enough to use.       We also have lunch in between there, but right now we are having supper. I go back to the pie car for my meal. We only have a little bit for supper because we will be performing afterwards.       When we all finish (which didn't take long, due to our meal size) , we go on stage for the big act. After a couple acts, I come on with the horses. I have them dance around and then I feed them some apples and carrots. Then some riders hop on their backs and I have the horses run around in a circle. My act is done. Me and the horses more off stage and let the other actors perform.       After we're all finished, the audience leaves and we go to sleep. Once I get into my bed, I wish I could tell my family and friends about my great act. I can't do that, though. We don't get to see home very much, so I just go to sleep in my trailer. . . .

Life's a Circus    Source #1      Bella Castini is a circus performer. She travels 20,000 miles in seven months a year. She works from day to night. Here's what she does when she wakes up: 7:00 A.M. she wakes up, gets dressed, and goes to the pie car for pancakes and bacon. The rest of the crews are setting up the lights, and music for their next show for the night. 9:00 A.M. Is school time. A one-room schoolhouse travels with them while they are on tour. Like any other school, this one has computers, tests, and report cards. Many of Bella's classmates can speak different languages like: French, Russian, and Italian. 3:00 P.M. After school, the clowns let Bella play with their unicycles and with their juggling balls. Then, she starts to play with her dog, Noodle. Bella has always wanted to be on a soccer team, but they dont stay at one place long enough. 3:30 P.M. After she plays with Noodles, she feeds, grooms, and waters the horses that are in the show with them.          Bella is working on leaping from a trampoline onto a horse's back. The other children are practicing to juggle and do acrobatics. 6:30 P.M. Bella and her family go to the pie car and eat dinner when their done practicing. They have to do 10 shows a week. 10:30 P.M. The show is over and everyone is tired.  Two more days and then they will set off to another town. 12:00 A.M. Bella is thinking about the end of the tour session. She wants to go home already but the tour isn't over. Bella doesn't really know if she still wants to be a circus performer when she grows up.                                                                       Becoming a Circus Performer            Source #2      Kidzworld spoke with one of the performer about how it felt being in a circus. Her name was Philippa Hayball. She is an acrobat and dancer with Cirque du Soleil's circus show, Quidam. Not just anyone can join the circus, you have to have a special kind of talent. When Philippa was five years old, she was in circus acts already. She did musical theatre and ballet. When Philippa was 11, she knew she just wanted to be a circus performer, so she gave up on everything else and concentrated on her dancing and performing. Philippa has worked all over the planet including, Australia and Japan and all over North America. Circus performers have to travel ont eh road with 100 more people who are in the circus.            Philippa always gets a thrill from performing in front of an audience. She says you can see the audience being transported to another world. There are some drawbacks in being in the circus. Circus performers dont spend a lot of time at home, and they have to work for very long days. When they're on tour, they can't really call anywhere home because they go to a lot of different places. Circus performers are always thinking about the next show. Philippa says that she misses her home and she doesn't see her family that much either. She says that when you're a circus performer, you have to work very long hours and they have to work weekends too.

Living in a Circus                Has your mom ever said to you, 'We live in a circus?' Well my friend Rose knows that a real circus is harder that you think.            On stage, circuses may look like all fun and games, but Rose knows it's not! Her day begins when she wakes up at seven o' clock. She gets dreasses and heads out to the pie care for breakfeast.            She often has typical food for breafeast. She might have bacon, or cereal. At around nine she goes to school. She has a traveling school with kids that don't speak just one language. Since Rose travels to perform at so many countries and speaks many languages. Her school still has tests, computers, and report cards, but its way more fun!            Three o' clock school is over, and she has a short break. She plays with the clowns, then she trys riding their unicycles. Three forty five is when she practrices for the show. She goes over her routine and then wait.            Six thirty. Dinner time! Rose hasn't eaten all day and is starving. However, she can't eat much because she has to perform.            Seven is show time. She does her stunts, and once again, she was nervous for nothing. Ten thirty show's over. And she has to clean up. At twelve shes in bed, fast asleep.                 Rose has a hard circus life, but it must be fun. I wish we could stay together, but she had her crazy, circus life, and I have my normal, life life.

Being a circus preformer sure can be a lot of work! I thought as I groomed the horses, who had just finished practicing for tonight's show.       'Cassidy!' I heard my mother calling. 'Honey, we're heading to the pie cart for dinner! The show is starting soon!'   I run after my mother and father and my sister, Amber, and soon we reach our destination.       As soon as we walk inside, Buddy the Clown greets us warmly.       'Ah, how are you, my dear Hillers? Sarah,' he turned to my mother,'how is your tightrope walking coming along? James,' now he turned to my father and clapped his enormous hand over my father's thin shoulder. 'I've seen you practicing your act where you'll juggle flames. Such perfect timing: tonight's show will be one of our best!'   My father laughed as Buddy removed his hand from his shoulder and now placed it on my head.      'Cassidy, are you excited for tonight's show? I can't wait to see you two somersault off Daisy The Elephant. That must take a lot of bravery!' He patted my head, as if I were a young child. People treat me differently just because I'm younger, but I'm twelve and very far from being the youngest one in the circus. 'Amber, your acrobatics are looking exceptional!' Amber is fourteen, only two years older than me, but she makes me feel as if she were another mom to me.        After we finish eating, we head to the main tent, called the Big Top. We are already in our costumes, and we all wait for the show to begin. My mother ties her long, fiery red hair back. The ringmaster steps out, welcomes the audience, and anounces the first act: James Hiller. Dad steps out into the spotlight and begins his act. At the end, my hands hurt from applauding. His act was fabulous!       Several more acts follow, including my mother and sister, until finally, it is my turn.      I step out into the center of the ring. The audience quiets, completely. This has never happened.      One man in the audience shouts out. 'That kid couldn't be older than nine! I came here to see a circus, not a ballet recital! She's going to get hurt!' Several others shout in agreement.       I hear my mother gasp from backstage. Out of the corner of my eye, I see my father, looking confused.       What is going on? I thought.       The ringmaster attempts calming the audience, but it is useless. 'Let's see your act, little girl! I am in the mood for some Girl Scout presentation.' The audience roared with laughter. I felt the anger boiling up inside of me. 'Ok, I will show you my act! Come on, Daisy!' I signaled for the elephant to come.       'Ok, just like we practiced.' I whispered in Daisy's ear as I climbed on her back. I rembered everything I had learned. I had to show this wild audience I was not a little kid, I was a talented young woman!          I gave Daisy a little kick, and she ran like the wind in circles around a small circular platform, where I will land. I slowly counted down. 5...4...3...2...1...       I remebered everything, even tucking in my chin. I did 6 flips and landed perfectly in the center of the platform.      The audience sat for a minute, speechless, then suddenly everyone, even the man who had called me a little girl, was clapping. I felt nothing but sheer pride and deep satisfaction. Not only had I done perfectly on my act, but I had proved everyone wrong. I was no longer a little girl. I was a confident young woman.

The Circus Story             Hi, my name is Abigale Bulginni and my whole life is a circus. You may think that being in a circus is spectacular, amazing kooky, tops up crazy, and a one in a life time opportunity but it's really not. Here I'll show you.            Having the opportunity of being in a circus is great but to become you have to sacrifice some of the other dreams that you might have. When I was 9 years old I always dreamed that I will become an international singer and when I was 12 I always wanted to be a nurse.            15 I went to the circus. It was amazing! Ever since I knew I had to be either a fierce lion tamer, a daredevil tight roper, or a legendary trapeze artist. When I told my mom and dad about my dream they were full on with me they paid for ballet lessons, track in field, and swimming lessons.            When I became 19 I signed up for the circus. They put me in a dark room with blue curtains and only one little hole window pouring in dim and dusty light. The employ hit a lever (which I guess was the spotlight) and a bright light the shade of lightning hit my face. Immediately I re-flexed my eyes by shading it with my arm. The employ responded ' Bright eh.' I shook my head. ' Well then wait in tell you meet the boss, he's wonderful!' said the employ sarcastically. He then left the room. I suddenly became very frightened. After 10 minutes a man with a purple, green, and orange tucks and a completely bald head came in. He had a snigger on his face making himself look completely dumb. I couldn't help but laugh a little. The man suddenly shouted out ' WHAT ER YOU LOOKING AT BOZO!' I then saw his big fat pigs belly. I couldn't help but laugh again. He began shouting for an hour strait and than he stopped and became silence. Then he said ' Dance.' I didn't do anything in the shock of how he he just suddenly became dumb. He yelled 'DANCE.' I suddenly caught my train of thought and started doing my most recent and advance ballet moves I knew. When I ended I could see he was not impressed. I suddenly thought that my dream would come to an end. ' The names Gogachi Panini kid.' I stopped thinking where have I heard that name before. I would do a front aerial and then and front walkover and the out of the front walkover front hand spring stepout. I would then go to the end of the beam and put one foot on and one foot off the end and from there a backhandspring stepout into a back aerial.       I then thought of more.
