There is a girl named Alexis, and she is making up her mind if she wants to join the circus or not. 'I don't know Hunter' said Alexis talking to her brother. 'Why not!' exclaimed Hunter. 'You are in shape, have good balance, and you get to travel the world!' Alexis was walking around her house trying to decide. Then, Alexis said she would join the circus tomorrow. Her parents said it was ok, and they went to bed.       The next morning Alexis and her family went to the circus sign-ups. Alexis was really nervous. Then her mother said 'Hello my daughter would like to join the circus. Is this where we sign in?' There was a big man in a white shirt and he nodded. The man lead Alexis and her family to a tent that was filled with people all over the world lining up to sign in for the circus. 'Are you sure you want to join the circus?' asked Alexis's father. 'Yes. I want to perform in the circus.' said Alexis.       A man blew his whistle and everybody went to him. 'Anybody who is joining the circus go in that corner.' Everybody went over there inclouding Alexis. He pointed to Alexis and said 'Whats your talent?' He asked. 'Ummm umm' Alexis didn't really have a talent so she blurted out 'Walking on the tightrope' she said. 'Ok you go over there' he said.       She walked on the tightrope very well. She didn't fall once.' Ok we will be leaving for our first tour tomorrow.' He said. 'TOMORROW!!!' Alexis screamed. They all ran back to their places to practice more. Alexis said goodbye to her parents. Then she went to practice. She was sad that she wouldn't see her parents for a while, but she was happy she was joining the circus.

Facts about the Circus   What is it like to be a circus preformer? Well, it contains hard work and a lot of dedication and you must have the right body type. Story about the circus By: Hallie Solie                                                                                                                                                                                           People probably could look at me and think that I was not a circus preformer. I don't ike the cold stares people give my mom when we go out in public with our face paint on. I don't want to be in the circus, but it is seomthing that I love and can't quit! I first joined the circus when I was 4. My parents wanted to keep me at a reasonable age to join the circus because there were so many different stunts involved. I first started meeting with a dance and gymnastics teacher every day, every week. We practiced keeping the beat and ometimes even different stunts. Soon when I was 8 I could do any gymnastics trick that anyone asked me. I was a terrific gymnast/ dancer and I officially joimed the circus after that. The first time I did a stunt it was revolting and unrealistic. I swung from bar to bar until I reached the end of the fish net. it was so scary yet so fun that I wanted to keep on doing it until I died. When I fell I just got right back up. My mom called me Wonder Women. Now, its different.       I get to have my own part in the show! I will be doing gymnastics AND dance! It will be so much fun! It was totally worth 10 years of waiting! I guess since I am 14 I am old enough to run the show! My first dance was a major hit! People loved it and applaud me loudly! It was the most beautiful clap I have ever heard in my entire preforming life. I would have to do a gymnastics act later tonight. My gymnastics act was even better! The claps were louder and more real. Back tucks and Front tucks were the main idea of what I was doing. People wistled and screamed my name! If I could do this all my life I would. Our next tour is in Boston ( I read my bosses planner  ) I hope they liked our act as much as Florida did!         Boston tour wasn't any different accept for my routine! The crowds applaud me like Florida did and they also screamed my name! Finally, people decided it was my time to do something that I wouln't do in a million years, I ran through the ring of fire! Johnny Cash blared through the radio and I looked at that small ring and jumped with all my  might. The fire burned me but it was something I could fit through. I guess I found my new circus act out.

Circus Life                                                               By Teagan           I like being in the circus but it is very difficult. It is very fun but I never can call a place home or join a sports team. I will tell you how fun and difficult a circus life can be.           6:30 am  I wake up and get dressed in my acrobat suit and go into the food car and eat pancakes with the clowns. The clowns are fun to eat with but they always want to play with their food. A lot of times the human cannonball man makes the pancakes.         7:15 am I start practicing my acrobat routine with my brother. After I finish practicing for the night show I play with the clowns. I love to ride their unicycles. Happy the clown showed me how to ride one. Happy is my favorite clown because he always wants to play boardgames with me.         8:45 am School starts I usually learn about math, science,geography and reading. Some times we have a lot of homework and if I need help I usually ask my mom, dad or Happy.Whats really fun is that for recess we get to play with the monkeys. My favorite monkey in named Ty, he is the smallest of all the monkeys.         2:30 pm Schools over and I have to start doing my chores. My chores are to feed all of the animals and practice with them so they are ready for the 5:45 and 9:30 show. I practice with the tigers to jump through a ring of fire. I don't really have to practice with the elephants because they don't really do anything people just do tricks on them. Last I practice with the monkeys, they do acrobatic and tightrope acts. It is actually kind of fun to practice with the monkeys.          3:00 pm I have my meal before the show. I eat with the clowns and my brother, mom and dad. My mom is an animal trainer and my dad is a tight rope walker. I have to eat my supper at 3:00 pm because if would eat right before I do my acrobatic act I might get sick during the 5:45 show.         4:30 pm  We start setting up the stage. It is horrible setting up the stage for every show because when we tour the world  we have to set up each time we move cities. It is really hard for me to carry the big safety net for my acrobat performance. It must way 100 pounds!         5:45 pm We start the show. That's my favorite part because all of the hard training will pay off. It is very exciting being an acrobat because it fells like you are flying through the air and just when you are going to hit the ground I get swooped up by my brother.             8:30 pm We just finished the show. It was super fun, I love performing in front of people. All of the performers get a quick break before we all have to do the 9:30 show. I've always thought the 9:30 show was to late at night but I still have to do it anyway.         9:30 pm We have to start the 9:30 show. I know I said I love doing my acrobatic show but I hate doing it all over again. I'm really tired after the first show but I still have to do everything again! It is horrible.         12:00 am All of the shows are over for the day and I am pooped. Everything I do is super tiring And I have to do it all twice! It is super fun to be in the circus but it also has a lot of down sides.

Margo Marasigan lives in a  big trailer with her family.Margo and her family travels around the world,and performs night shows in cities,like Las Vegas,Manila,Santa Maria.Margo always has a typical day just like her circus performer friends.She has to do work everyday with her family.Margo misses her home in the Philippines and wishes to go back.                            Here is a typical day for Margo:                 8:00 A.M. Margo wakes up gets dressed and eats breakfast with her friends at a trailer where circus performers eat.Some days they eat pancakes,and bacon,but most of the time they mostly eat rice,sausages,and spam.                    9:00 A.M. School time.They have a one-room schoolhouse that travels with them.The schoolhouse has things that a regular school has,like computers,textbooks,and report cards.Everyday they learn new things in Math,English,and Social Studies.Sometimes when they have some extra time they learn French,Russian,or maybe Italian languages.           2:00 P.M. School is over.The clowns let Margo play with their unicycles.And sometimes she juggles balls,or maybe bowling pins.Margo also have a puppy named Etho,which she plays and walks him in the nearby park.           2:39 P.M.Chores and practice.Margo feeds the horses,waters the plants,and cleans her room if it's messy.Her dad practices horse back acts.She is practices somersaulting off a running horse.She is also working on leaping from a trampoline onto the horse's back.          5:30 P.M.Dinner time.Tonight Margo ate Hamburgers for dinner.She didn't ended up finishing the hamburger because shows about in an hour and they need to get ready.               6:30 P.M. Showtime.Margo loves doing tricks while she was at horseback.She loves how everytime when Margo makes eye contact to them the jump up from their seats to cheer them on.Margo is always used to performing at night and performing a matinee on Wednesdays.           10:00 P.M.Show's over.Margo is exhausted.As she was walking back to the trailer,she passes the circus office.Two Days from now,they will set up in another state.

''Oh shoot!''thought Joseph. His parents had just told him that they were going to go to the circus that Joseph worked at to watch him perform!Joseph has been working for the Alveni circus for two months, just enough to get the hang of it, but now that his parents were coming he felt like he had learned nothing.         There was only one thing to do. Practice, Practice, Practice.So Joseph left with an alarming,''By!'', hopped on his bike, and started pedaling. He checked his watch, 9:34 a.m., when he looked up, all he saw was the red and blue of the circus tent.On his way in he waved to Matt, his best friend out everyone at the circus. He quickly climbed up the ladder, and hung on to the trapeze. Before starting he took a big, deep, slow, breath. While he swayed he did amazing flips, alternating as if time didn't even exist anymore. This is how he always felt on the trapeze, but while he swung he saw his parents along with all of the fans. He was still looking when he plummeted into the net.          Oh no! He had forgotten he had a performance this morning!          When he woke up he heard,''And now, Joseph  Kelleman!''What the heck was going on!He looked down and saw Matt giving him two thumbs up, and managing a slight smile. Ohhh, Matt had brought him up here. Well, now or never. He grabbed on, and he did it!While he swayed back and forth he saw his parents smiling. Well, he saw them smiling upsidedown, but either way, it was success.

I live in the circus, just about all my life Ive been here, its hard but it can be very fun. Every morning its get up, get dressed, clean up after the animals, do your chores, eat breakfast, do some school work, practice, eat lunch, get ready for show, practice more for show and do the show.            I have to live like this everyday, it can get annoying, but you can't quit my family is in the circus with me. They can tell you how hard it is too, the clowns when I have time will sometimes let me ride their unicycles, its hard luckily I don't have to do that for a show, then I have to care for the animals more.             You will be surprised by how much you have to do shows, every few days you put on a new show. I have to help put up the tents, bring the animals in, fed the animals, get everything to the places they need to be and always be prepared for the worst in the circus life.             There are many animals we have to take care of, leopards, lions, tigers, elephants, chimpanzees and more but there are a lot of them. We have special trainers for the animals to do their acts with, I take care of the horses and elephants mostly, the elephants are the smelliest animal I'll ever meet!               My act is standing on two running horses, and then when they start getting farther apart I do the splits with my feet on different horse backs. Many of my family members travel with us, and other people I know come with us. Many of the people in the circus are either from my family, or my neighborhood I lived in.              Back when I lived in my neighborhood I went to sleep at 8 p.m. but here, I don't get to sleep till 12 in the morning. Living in the circus is hard, and it takes forever to get used to, but when you do get used to it, you won't ever go back.             Bad part is, if you wan to be an acrobat, you have to be right body shape and have determination. Some people join for fun, some wanting to see the world while having a fun job, many come by themselves and have no family with them. When you come by yourself, it feels like you are a stranger in a world of people knowing each other.            Life in the circus can be hard, after awhile of living with it you will start to like it. Being i the circus isn't just doing fun things all the time, it has to do hard work, determination and many chores and jobs you need to do, so don't think its all merry good time here, think and study what you do before you join.

Life in the circus isn't as easy as most think it is. Learning the circus routines is hard because you need to be on time when you are doing tricks and need to be confident in how you are doing. Circus performers do 10 shows a week and travel 20,000 miles in seven months just to do performances. All you do is work from sunup to sundown and after that, they still have to perform. Most circus performers are wiped out after they are done performing. They even cant go to bed until 12:00. Imagine riding a unicycle and doing a trick at the same time. Well that is what they do. They are always away from home and I cant even imagine being that home sick.           When you are in the circus, you live in a trailor. You sleep and groom yourself in there too. When circus performers wake up, they eat breakfast in a pie car which is where performers eat their breakfast, lunch, and dinner. Can you imagine that?! Since performers perform at night, they dont eat much dinner before they go out on stage or else they will puke. They perform weekly plus a matinee which is an afternoon show. When most performers have nothibng to do, they are practicing. Kids practice juggling and scrobatics while adults practice flying up in the air and balancing on wires.            Now you know how hard it is in life in the circus. If you want to join the circus, make sure you are confident and ready for any expectations coming your way because you are in for a ride. Also be strong and practice practice practice. Remember, practice makes perfect.

Your father and I both love you so much so we don't want to see you at a young age.'           'Well, I am an adult now so I have my own decisions of what I want to be. A few days later, Bob went to his room and packed up his clothes and everything else he needed.Since Bob had his own car, he took off driving to the Bellini Circus. When he arrived, he applied to join the circus. The manager said,' If you want to be in the circus, you'll need years of practice,'           ' Sure, I am all ready. I don't care if I have to practice for years, being a circus performer is my dream.', replied Bob.            The manager took  Bob to the room where all the newcomers belong. ' Bob, this will be the room that you practice in. If you need any help you can ask the teacher here, Jimmy.' Bob wanted to learn how to juggle so he took three balls and tried to juggle. He failed like 300  times but he did't give up. He walked up to Jimmy and asked,' Hey, Jimmy I need help on juggling balls.'            ' Jimmy took two balls and started juggling. See, Bob the trick is that you always keep your eyes on the balls so you won't loose control. Start just with two balls, learn from the basics.'             After two years of practice, Bob finally became a professional circus performer. He began juggling rings and walking on tightropes. He performed at the Bellini circus for five years. In the sixth year, he missed home. In the circus, there are no phones or any devices that can contact your relatives.  He started crying, whining that he wants to go home. He tried to sneek out of circus but got caught for about ten times.             At the performance in San Francisco, where his home is. He was performing walking on tightropes. He felt homesick when he was walking on the rope and he fell off. The manager annouced ' Sorry, one of our professional performer fell off the rope, named Bob.              A woman from the audience got out of her seat and walked to the performance area. It was Bob's mom. She looked at the performer named Bob and there it was, her son, laying down on the floor moaning in pain. ' Oh, poor Bob, if you had listened to me, you wouldn't be in a mess like this.            She dialed 911 and the ambulance came. They carefully put Bob in the ambulance and brought him to the hospital. The doctor said that he had his bones fractured in his right leg. When Bob woke up, he saw his mother. ' Oh, mom. Am I glad to see you. I was crying almost everyday because I missed home. Well, here I am, home in San Francisco. Oh by the way, thank you, mom for rescuing me from the circus. It was a nightmare! There are no phones to call home and barely any free time. All you do there is just practice, practice, and pactice.If I had just listened to you I wouldn't be here, in a hospital bed where my leg is fractured.'             When Bob's leg healed he went home and apologized to his mother and father for not listening to them. Later on, when Bob wanted a new job, he will always ask his parent if they agree or not.

The circus By: Anna V. Roth                                                                                                                   There was a girl named Anna she was part of a circus she was about 11 years old. Anna's dad owed a circus  when Anna was born she was naturally acrobat and so was her little sister named Gwyn.                   Anna and Gwyn were as graceful as birds flying threw the sky when they were practicing. One day Anna and Gwyn's dad said, 'girls how about you practice a very special trick for Saturday.' Anna asked her dad why an extra special trick is some one really important going to come to their show? The girls father said yes the president was coming to their show and is going to bring his daughter and it is her birth day.               When Saturday came around Anna and Gwyn were both so nerves to preform in front of the president. when Anna got up on the bar and swung and did 3 somersaults and a pike then Gwyn grabed her hands. Then jumped back on to the plat form the crowed went wild. The president's daughter told her dad 'This is the best birthday i have ever had' her dad almost started to cry.

Every day at the circus I wake up  early, to begin for a hard day. I have to go to school, do chores, practice, and perform. First, I go to school. Then, I do my chores and practice. After that, I eat, and after that I perform. The long show is finally over at ten thirty, and I am so tired! I am finally in bed at twelve A.M., which might seem late, but it's not when you get up at nine.     To get into the circus, we all had to have some sort of special talent that we were really good at. The rooms we stay in are small, so we can't really have any big animals as pets.     We move around a lot. There are bad things and good thing about being able to move around. The good things are getting to travel the world. It makes geography class a lot easier. Another good thing is getting to see and meet new people every week. A few bad things are not really staying in one place for long. Also, not being able to stay and enjoy being in the presents of one place for a long time. Last, we are away from home a lot.     We work with many different people from all across the world. Some speak different languages, but it if they seem nice we still figure out ways to be friends.

Last year I had ran away from family to join a circus. At first I thought it would be fun, but now that I'm in a circus I see that it is very challenging. Since I once worked at zoo, I agreed I would take care of the animals and train them. Its VERY hard work!!      Every morning I feed the horses, lions, seals, and chimpanzees. Next I go get somthing to eat at the pie car. Then I help set up the tents, lights, and music for tonights show.  A few other trainers and I work with the animals. Yesterday we got a new animal, a cheetah I named Namarah. I got to work with Namarah on jumping through a ring of fire. She did really good!!!!      That night people came through the tent talking, laughing and guessing what show we might put on for them. We were all nervous for the big show. We had planned to do things we had never done before! As Seth, the director of our circus walked out in front of the big crowed and started anouncing some things that we might do tonight, I help Namarah into her outfit.      The first to go out was Zan, our chimpanzee, and his trainer, Bob. As Zan juggled bowling pins and rode a unicycle I ran out with Namarah. Namarah jumped over obsticles and through tunnels. I heard some of the audiance go 'OOOHHH' and 'AAAHHH'. Namarah stopped where she was supposed to, to start getting ready to jump through the Ring of Fire. I set the tiny ring a couple yards away from Namarah and set it on fire. She stared at me, fear in her eyes. I mouthed ' Do it just like we been practicing.' She seemed to understand. I saw her load back and fire herself right and the ring. Then she leaped, I held my breath and closed my eyes.       All of a sudden I heard screams of joy and clapping. I open my eyes to see Namarah standing right next to me, rubbing her head against my leg. I bend down and look her right in the eyes and say 'You did great!!!!!!.' Then I kiss her on top of the head, and she licks me in the face. I stand back up again and take a bow, I see Namarahs eyes sparkle with joy.     I learned that a circus life is tough but Namarah always makes it fun.

My Grand Performance                     This was it. This was my last circus act for the rest of my life. I had been training for this one for months. It was the biggest performance we had done yet. It was called the The Shining Star. I was waiting at the end of the tight rope, waiting for the signal that let me on. I was extremely nervous, but excited at the same time. I was supposed to be on a unicycle, and juggling five balls across the tight rope. The horses and the elephants were out. It was my turn. I mounted my unicycle. I made sure that I had the five balls in my hand, and started out on the rope. I wobbled at first but I don't think anyone noticed.                              I Smiled at the crowd and started to juggle. I started out with three, then four, (I was doing great!) then......... I was falling.....spinning forward,and sideways, I landed on the trampoling with a SMACK!!!, and fell off of it. I luckily landed on my feet. I wasn't badly hurt, on the outside. The inside of me was what hurt the most. I had let my whole team down. I just smiled, and ran out. Back stage, everyone crowded aruond me. They all asked me if I was okay. I told them all that I was sorry, and I had let them down. We were sure to lose the contest now.                         At the end of the show, the announcer told the winner. It was us!!!! Everyone cheered! It was great!! I had no idea how though... I mean.. I fell. The other team did perfect. Later I talked to the announcer and asked him how we won. He told me that I did absolutely wonderful, and the way that I had jumped off the rope, spun in the air, landed on the trampoline, and bounced off with a perfect landing on the feet! I was amazed! Did he really think that I had done that on purpose?! I started to tell him what had really happened, but the crew came in and told me I was late to celebrate! I guess falling wasn't so bad after all.

I opened my eyes. Just another average Monday in circus life, or so I thought at that time. I sighed, and started to slide out of my bed on a circus trailer. I looked at the clock on the wall-6:51 A.M. I decided that, since I normally got out of bed at 7:00 A.M., nine more minutes of sleep wouldn't hurt. I plopped back down onto my bed and started to close my eyes.        I was awoken again by a light knock on my door. I bolted out of bed and looked at the clock again-7:16 A.M. I had overslept for the first time! I quickly got dressed and went to the pie car. There, I found that most of the performers were already done with breakfast. The ringmaster noticed me and said, 'Is this the first or second time you overslept, Emily?' I sighed once more when the ringmaster had gone. The day was already starting out badly.         I quickly finished breakfast and went to the schoolhouse. Fortunately, that went well, unlike when I got up and, as I would soon find out, my practice and performance time.        At 3:30 P.M., school was over, and it was break time. I saw that we had arrived in our destination-Kansas City. I played a short while with my teacup chihuahua, Teacup, and started practice early, thinking that would make up for me oversleeping. Unfortunately, that was not true.       I began my practice as normal. I started to jump from a trampoline onto a horse's back. After several times of doing this, I began to relax and daydreamed that nobody had noticed me oversleep. My daydreams eventually evolved into a dream of seeing my family and living back in Miami, Florida. Oh, how I missed that time. But I had taken a liking to acrobatics and determinedly joined the circus when I was 11. Now I had been in the circus for five years now. I have traveled all over North and South America. Now, still daydreaming, I leaped again from the trampoline, imagining I was bouncing down the stairs. 'THUMP!' I was jolted from my daydream by pinpricks of pain shooting up my leg.       I was surprised to find myself sprawled in the dirt, wondering how I had gotten there. I had thought I was jumping down the stairs to the a kitchen. I then remembered that I was in the circus, and I was practicing jumping off a trampoline onto a horse's back. I realized I had jumped straight off a trampoline 15 feet in the air with no horse to support my fall.       Wincing, I tried to get up. I made the mistake of putting my weight on my injured right leg and collapsed. I heard other performers arriving for practice. A man leading an elephant saw me first. He ran to me and called to the others for the ringmaster. He then also left to find the ringmaster. No! I thought. I already have embarrassed myself once, but I will not be embarrassed twice! I slowly got up, and started to limp around. After a while, the pain in my leg subsided, so I decided to continue practicing as if nothing had happened. The ringmaster arrived with a worried face. I rushed up the trampoline.       Seeing me seemingly all right, the ringmaster's expression changed from worried to confusion. He then became angry. He turned to the man who was leading the elephant and started to scream something about tricking him. I just continued to practice, trying to ignore the pain in my leg.        After dinner, we all started to prepare for the show. By now, the pain in my leg had nearly gone, so I decided I could make it though the show. My mind insisted on it-performing in a circus show, having fun performing, and seeing the audience so absorbed into my performance were the reasons I joined.        I went with the others backstage. After a while, I heard the announcer announce my name. I took a deep breath. In. Out. Shakily and painfully, I got to my feet. I went in the direction of the stage. In. Out. I emerged onstage, and I heard the audience clapping. In. Out. I climbed the trampoline and waited for my horse, Creamy, who was named for the color of her fur, mane, and tail. Not yet. Not yet. NOW! I jumped off the trampoline just as my leg bent in an awkward position-the position my leg was in when I fell at practice.        I lurched in midair, and was about to slam into the ground. My life is over, I thought. I had forgotten about the safety net, and had not set it up. But just then, Creamy doubled back and, amazingly,  caught me. The audience clapped again, thinking this was part of the show. I rode Creamy back backstage while murmuring to her softly, praising her.        When the show was over, the ringmaster praised Creamy too, saying I was lucky to have such a brilliant horse. If not, I would have died that day.        Nearly a month has passed since then. My leg has long since healed, and I continue to practice and perform successfully with Creamy, my life-saving friend and companion.

Today, i'll be sharing some information about the circus. The circus let's you travel places you've never been before while travaling with your new family.                                    You should join the circus because you can travel to new places. Here are a few reasons why . First, you will be able to go on many adventures with your 'family.' For example, you may go to Hawaii for a performance and have fun snorkling. Next, you will be able to try new foods. You can try some exotic Chinese food that you have never tried before. Finally, you will be able to explore new cultures. You can go to India and learn about their culture and festivals like Diwali.                        Join the circus because you can make a new and supportive family. Not convinced, i'll give you a few reasons. First, you will have many people who will care for you and love you just the way you are. About twenty years ago, I was a student in Lark Creek elementary school. My teacher clapped her hands and said, 'Students, I have an important announcement to make. Our school has won one rare ticket from the five to attend the Bellini Circus in the front row seats! That's right, one of you very lucky students will be able to win the free ticket by writing the best essay in class'.       As I walked home with my best friend we both discussed how we would write a essay. The instant I reached home, I started to write my essay:       'If anyone would think special talents were gifted to you, that is wrong. Even people in the circus must work harder than ever; often sacrificing extra time with friends and family to achieve their dream of performing in the circus. Take Philippa for example. When she was 11, she had her heart set on being a performer. She gave up everything and concentrated on her dance and performing. This is how to achieve your dreams.       Being part of a circus doesn't mean a free pass from school, in fact the one room classroom has everything a regular class has from a whiteboard to tests. Since circus performers are from around the globe, classrooms are often filled with a 'mixed bag' of students. The circus performers live in a trailer where there is a pie car (it is like a restaurant), a classroom, and of course a home for performers to live in.                                                                                                              When school is over it is time for some fun; circus style. The children get to see what the others are training and finally, kids get to try some tricks them self. People in the circus must be daring and adventurous. Tricks may include: leaping form a trampoline onto a horse's back, somersaulting from a horse's back, acrobatics, juggling, walking baby leopards on leashes, and training animals such as elephants, lions and chimpanzees.       Like all other jobs, working in a circus has ups and downs. One of the upsides is that you get to travel around the world. Performers get to meet people from around the world with interesting backgrounds. Another pleasure is the thrill of performing in front of a live audience. The downside of working in a circus is that circus performers  work for long periods of hours. In addition, performers are away from their family and home.       As you an see circus performers have a different, but somewhat hard life. If you work hard, your dream can come true'.       I looked down at my essay, and realized that I didn't care to win. Writing this essay was the gift after all. I had learned so much about the circus and realized that I might want to be there. I might want to do that. Being a glamorous star of the circus became my dream that day.       The next day, I walked to school with my essay in my hand. I told myself, 'I don't want to win, I have already won a big dose of inspiration'.       I handed in my essay in the morning as the teacher smiled. In an hour the teacher would announce the winner. As the clock ticked, it was hard for me to concentrate. Finally, the teacher announce the winner, and it was me. I had won a front seat ticket to the Bellini Circus. My career seemed to fly from then on. I got to meet Philippa, and she gave me a few words on how to succeed. I worked harder than ever at gymnastics now. I decided that I would awe the audience with my difficultly and flexibility. That is how I reached my dream and became The star of the circus. I was nicknamed Philippa #2. I tell youngsters around the world that it all started with a little dose of inspiration.

My name is Bob Smith.  I am an 11-year-old circus performer.  I travel around North America with my family.  Circus life is far from all fun and games.  Every day, and sometimes twice a day, we entertain a large audience for many hours.  Everyone works from dawn to dusk.  Here is our normal schedule:       6:30 A.M.: Wake up and prepare for yet another long day.  We head to the pie car for a quick breakfast.        8:00 A.M.: Time for a long, boring day of school.  All the kids are packed into an extremely small trailer, which makes learning hard.  Just like a normal, non-traveling school, our school has tests and progress reports.        3:30 P.M.: School's out!!!  But the work is just beginning.  We have to practice for tonight's show, and for the following shows.  While the crew continues to set up for the show, all the performers practice their respective stunts, such as walking on a tightrope, training wild animals, juggling objects, and jumping on to and off of a horse.  Beinng a good circus performer takes, balance, determination, and concentration.       6:00 P.M.: Everybody returns to the pie car for a light dinner.       7:00 P.M.: Showtime.       10:30 P.M.: The show is finally over.  The audience really enjoyed the performance!  I managed to juggle three bowling pins!  However, I am very tired and eager to go to bed.       11:00 P.M.: I hop into bed.       Circus life is a very tough life.  But it is also very fun. So despite the downsides of circus life, I enjoy it and am eager to take the stage for every performance.

April 12, 2010   10:30pm                                Dear Diary,                              Show is over! everyone loves this time of night. I finally get to sleep. Too bad I can't party in the pie car with everyone else because of mom and dad. Mom and dad are so mean to me. They say I have to be in the circus 'till I'm 65, and I can't party inthe pie car 'till I'm 18. And you know what? Today is my birthday. I'm turning 18 today, and I didn't even ggo to the party. They completly forgot. Maybe they don't even care about me..... I don't know.            I'm sorry I don't do this every day, but I barely get even a spare second in a week. From 7:00am to 10:30pm every day, I work and practice my horse riding standing and dismounting my horse, Shamrock. I don't even get a full education. I only do school work 3 hours a day, and right now I'm supposed to be in college.            Today my schedule was even worse. Mom made me practice during school, so I missed learning what an antacedent is. Dad made me do the heap of dishes in the pie car, because I didn't put my dish in the sink. Also, the director got mad at me when on of my bells flew off my bracelet Annie gave me last year. I don't even know if Annie is my friend or not. She just is kind to me. We're both the same age, and we have a lot in common, but she has been avoiding me lately.            Although, one part was good today. I finally did everything perfect on my routine during practice, but my directer didn't even notice I did it flawlessly. The only person(thing) that noticed me was Shamrock, and he was licking and slobbering all over me.           Today was horrible, with one good part, but in the circus isn't that bad, especially when I can actually talk to someone(something) that will listen.

My name is Michael Smith. First, I will tell you what a normal day of circus life is like.       6:30 A.M.  I wake up and go to the pie car to have breakfast. I usually have scrambled eggs and pancakes. Everyone is startingto set things up for tonight's show.       9:00 A.M. I go to school. I learn different languages, sometimes on a computer. When I travel the world, I'll have to know how to speak to the audience!       3:00 P.M.  School's over-I usually grab a quick snack and practice juggling or unicycle riding.           6:00 P.M. I have dinner and prepare for tonight's show when I'm finished.           10:30 P.M. The show is over. I am wore out. Tomorrow, I will have to perform again. Now, I'm off to bed.       Circus life can get stressful!               Now, I will tell you what a performance is like.                I wait for my que at the beginning of the show. When I get the signal that I'm suppost to perform, i run out from behind the tent curtain, do a couple of cartwheels as i go, and I get up on the trampolene. I have to jump on a charging horse.            The horse is released, and I get ready for the jump. when the horse gets close, I jump! If I time it right, I will land on the horse and I will be able to gain control of it. It is a terrifying trick, but I've gotten used to it!            Finally, Circus life can be stressfull and even risky at times. It is fun to watch the audience applaud me for my hard work, though. Circus life is stressful, but it is well worth it!

Tiara and the Lost Money                       Not long ago, a baby girl was born and named Tiara. She had long black hair and big brown eyes. Her lips were full and her eyelashes long. Her body shape looked as if it was good enough to be a gymnast. There was nothing more she could possibly want. She had her own room, painted rose pink. Her name was painted on one of the walls. By the time she was eight, she was spoiled rotten. She had candy in her room. She had decorations in her room. All the children at her school adored her because she would always get money from her mom, take it to school, and give them some or buy them something.             One day, when Tiara took money to school, she lost her money somewhere in the school. she asked everyone if they saw it but they all had no clue where it was. She began to cry. Everyone in the area looked at her and began whispering in each others ear. She could hear them say, 'Is she really crying over money? I can't be friends with a crybaby so everybody can be talking about me.' Could this be the end of her popularity? All because of crying? She stood up and told every one to stand up and empty their pockets. Right when she said that everybody did so, maybe she didn't lose her popularity after all. as soon as Joe emptied his pockets there it was, low and behold, Tiara's $50.00!              Everyone gasped. 'Joe, how could you?' everyone gasped. Joe apologized to Tiara but she did not forgive him. It is one thing to borrow, but stealing is not the way. Soon it was time to go outside for carpool. When Tiara got into the car she told her mom what happened. As long as Tiara had her money back her mom was not disappointed.

One day a regular  summer day in San Diego the wind was blowing the streets were buzzing and the circus was ready to do its Wednesday matinee. In the end this would not be a regular day in circus history to find out what happened in this wacky day in circus history read these paragraphs.         The people had just arrived to the Bellini circus people buying popcorn and cotton candy the performers getting ready for the show and the family's waiting impatiently for the show to start. The lead act was the clowns doing some jokes and some other stuff but just as the clowns ended the circus tent collapsed. People were going crazy this was just like when the Minnesota vikings stadium collapsed except there was nobody in the dome when that happened but today there were thousands of people. The circus director was going crazy so he called the fir department. When the fire department got there they evacuated the rest of the people that hadn't already left the structure. Then the manager soon found out all of the circus animals got loose so he had to call animal control to wrangle the animals. Then came news that some people got injured so we called the medics. They ended up being okay they were just minor injuries. There was still major chaos all around and in the tent.''What happened'' and ''What's going on'' were questions a lot of people had when leaving the venue. They found out that people outside the tent did something to make the tent collapse and fall. To this day nobody knows how the tent fell and who did it. It will probably remain unknown forever. At the end of it all nobody died and only one animal they didn't get back a baby elephant.

Hi. I work in a circus. My name is 'Alex the Acrobat.' (As you can probably tell) I play the part of an Acrobat. I work night and day. Most people think that being in a circus means that you get to play all the time, but that is not true. The circus is about hard work and dedication. I've been working at the circus for 10 years and I still haven't gotten the hang of the schedule.The circus may be a fun place to work at, too, despite all the bad stuff, but you still have to travel a lot of tedious road trips. You also have to put up with schools and colleges that are a little too much on the wacky side.                      If you're wondering why I chose to be an acrobat, my answer would be that doing all that work really pays off when you show all your awesome moves, like front flips and jumping off and catching yourself, to the world (where-as other jobs don't pay off as much).                     One really awesome thing that is probably the reason I joined the circus is that instead of sitting in a desk and looking at a book for geography, we get to see our geography lessons come to life as we travel the world, now that is something truly amazing. So if you're looking for a job and love to meet new people and do new things, why not the circus, you got nothing to loose.

Hello, I am Harold. Lots of people call me Harry. I am 10 years old and I am a circus performer. I entered the circus when I was 5 years old, I was very young to be a performer, in fact the youngest in the whole group of performers. I was recognized for my talent of being funny and being great at gymnastics. Today I am a clown and an acrobat. My back round is very interesting.       Right now I am getting ready for a show. In this show I am a clown. I usually juggle and make kids laugh. Sometimes on the set I make other actors laugh too. I n this show I will barely be on stage. Most of the time when I am on stage I am an acrobat. When I am a clown I tell jokes to kids and try to sell stuff. Since I am in the circus I do not get to see my family and it is very hard for me because I miss them so much. Lots of the other people that are in the circus like me even though I am much younger than them.       Circus life is very hard. You have to practice basically all day. This afternoon I practice for nearly four hours. before that I had a delicious breakfast with bacon and eggs in the pie cart. I am lucky to get such good food from the Pie cart. Lots of parts of being the circus is fun too because I get to be the clown and get to use unicycles and juggling balls and make people laugh. In the circus life is fun and hard.       This is it. It is time to go on stage. I only have one part on stage and it isn't very long. I can't wait. First I act as a mime and pretend I am in a box, even though I am not. Now I am done and I have to put my clown uniform on.       You have to change into new clothes very fast in the circus business. Now I am trying to sell cotton candy and other foods and condiments. It is pretty easy. Tonight I have sold lots of food and now I have to entertain the audience. I am now walking over to a baby. He is very cute. I have a great joke to pull on him. LIFE IN A CIRCUS                                                                  Life in a circus seems very fun, but it is very hard work. You can't just say I want to become a circus performer, you have to train for it. For instance, if you want to do acrobats, you have to have the right body and you have to train for it. If you want to do juggling you have to just train for it. It seems so easy, but sometimes it seems as if you kind of risk your life. Like if your somersaulting off of a running horse, that seems like your risking your life, but that's what trainings for.             It also seems that the circus performers are more your family then your regular family. It seems like this because you are traveling so much and your always away from home. You really have to put your heart in it and concentrate because if you don't, then you might mess up and you don't want that to happen in front of all those people.             And of course you don't just go to school and train, you have to do chores too. You might have to feed the animals, groom the animals, help clean up after every show, or just help get ready for every show. And when your in the circus you usually work from sun up to sun down. So your going to be busy every hour of the day.               It also seems that if your in the circus traveling all the time, you might get a really good experience if your paying attention. It seems like this because you get to travel all around the world. You would probably get to travel to Japan, Russia, Ireland, or even Australia.              And it seems that being in a circus makes you famous because you are well known, and people are amazed by what you can do, and since they're so amazed they tell every one to go see the show. Then when the word gets around, people start to know your name and ask for autograghs. And thats why I think that your famous when your a circus performer.               And when your on tour and away from home. It seems as if you really have no place to call home because your always moving from one place to another. Your going to always be thinking about how your going to do on tonights show, or how everyone else is going to do that effects you.               I've always wondered if the circus performers ever missed their real home and family. I've wondered this because they usually call their circus performing friends family and home. But who knows they might not.              And now that I've talked about how hard it is to be a circus performer, would you want to be a circus performer? If you do, then what would you do, would you do juggling or trapeze? What would you do in the long hours of a circus life?               And like I've said, performing in a circus seems very fun, but it is very hard work. It is also a great experience too. So if your interested in going to a circus, then go to one and see the amazing things they've worked so hard on.

Circus Day                 Angela Brown sat up, yawning. The sun was only just slowly rising up the hills. For a moment, she was confused. What am I doing here? she thought. Suddenly, the moments of the day before came rushing to her mind. She had been selected to perform in the Bellini Circus as an acrobat. She had been led to a trailer that she was to share with another acrobat, Betsy White. As if the thought had conjured her up, Betsy stood before her, calling  cheerfully,  'Time to get ready!'  The tall, freckled girl always seemed to have a smile. Angela quickly scrambled to change out of her pajamas. The shows were at night, so she didn't need her outfit yet.           Betsy showed her around the circus area after they went to the pie car for breakfast. At 9, they had school. Betsy enjoyed it thoroughly and made many friends, some of which came from different countries!           After school, Angela, Betsy, and their friends ate dinner and quickly changed into their outfits. Angela was exhilarated. She loved seeing the audience and feeling like they had come all the way just to see her! After the show, Angela changed out of her outfit. She crawled into bed and fell asleep immediately, she was so exhausted. She dreamed about the circus and the happy times she would  have.

My name is Amy,  I'm a circus performer and I have a very busy life, this is a normal day to me, when I get up in the morning, around 7:00 I go to the pie car and eat pancakes and bacon, then I get dressed and go to school at 9:00, after school ends I have very little time to play with my cat, Snicker doodle, and the clowns let me play with there equipment and then I'm off to practice for the coming nights circus.       After I practice, we go to the pie car once again for dinner, After dinner is when things settle down, I have time to play and have quality time with my family and then go to bed. Everyone seems to think that circus life is fun and high flying, well people who think that are wrong, circus life is really tough, for example, you have to have the right body,  talent and you have to be determined.       You cant go to the circus and expect to be a acrobat, lion tamer or stuff like that right off the bat, it takes lots of training to get to the point where you can actually perform in front of a live audience. If you want to be a good performer, you have to give up everything else and focus on the circus.        Although its a very tough and busy life for me and my family, it can also be very fun. When you are a performer you have the chance to travel the world, you meet lots of new people, and the people from the circus are like a family to me.        A downside to this life though, is that you don't really have a place to call your home. You are everywhere and your always thinking about the upcoming show. You work really hard for the circus and sometimes its not fun at all because you have to learn things that are hard for your body to do. You work a lot of long hours during the day and the weekends too.

One day, when I was walking to school, I saw a sign on the billboard way up high that said,'Are you ready for a circus in town?'I was surprised. I had never been to a circus. I was planning to go. But on the side of it, it said,  '$55.95 for each person or instead, make a poem about clowns, turn it in, and if you get an approval, you will win a free ticket to the circus.' There was no way I could get that money in time, I thought. Anyways, I only had $0.50 in my piggy bank. I made the right choice. I decided to make a poem.         During school, I was thinking about writing that poem. I wasn't paying attention to all the subjects my teacher had taught. As days and days passed on, I only had two days left until it was to late. At home, I finally picked up my pencil and started to write:                                                                                   Clowns                                                                         Victoria Kozuchi                                                Clowns are funny, Clowns can be colorful                                        Clowns can also come in various shapes and sizes                                   They make kids and babies laugh. They have big red noses.                             So what else can they do? They all have abilities just like me and you!               The next day, I turned it in. The manager liked it and approved it. I was so happy! I got two tickets for me and ....   I didn't have another person to go with. I thought to myself. Then, an answer came to me. On the following day when I was going to the grocery store, I found a girl who was staring at the same poster I saw. She seemed like she was from my school. I asked her if she was going to the circus. She said,'No, I don't have that kind of money.'I asked her if she wanted to come to the circus with me. She replyed,'Sure!'            It was the day of the circus. We didn't have front row seats, but we had second row seats. It was better than nothing. When the show started, the crowd was clapping and cheering. We seemed like we were both amazed at the juggling act and the circus acrobats. Soon horses came running up in the stage and they looked like bright, shiny unicorns. Lastly, a tightrope walker walked across the rope. It felt like he was going to fall, but he didn't. After the show, we met a clown. He made us both two heart shaped balloons. Caroline, the girl who came with me said,'Thank you very much.'and left. I'm sure I'll meet her at school.                                                                                                  THE END

It was finally my act. I was standing backstage, watching Miko, who was juggling, while Justice was flipping through never-ending rings of fire. My palms got really sweaty and I felt queasy as the crowd applauded and Miko and Justice bowed, because now was my act. Sandra stood beside me and recognized my fear. She grabbed my hand and we walked into the ring together. The lights shone on me so bright, I felt like I could pass out. The clapping sounded like mocking in my head. I couldn't tell what everyone was chanting, but it sounded like, 'You can't do it! You can't do it!' over and over again. Suddenly the bar slowly descended down, and I knew it was time. Sandra and I looked at each other, she smiled, I almost burst into tears. It was time.     We simutaneously grabbed the bar and sat upon it. It suddenly rised up and we were about 100 feet above the ground. My throat closed. No net, no pillows, nothing. If I fell, I would die. Blood everywhere. The lights dimmed, and a big bright one shone on us. Glowsticks on. Fear on maximum. This was it.      My legs wrapped around the bar, and I slowly, one by one, let my hands off. I hung upside down for about a minute, then grabbed the bar once again, but this time I was in a tear drop shape. My legs swung off the bar. 'Don't look down, don't look down!' I thought to myself. After several flips, the lights shut off, not quite pitch black. The audience clapped as the bar descended. Once it lowered down low enough that we could touch the ground, we let go and the bar dissapeared up into darkness. As the crowd kept applauding, I leaned over and whispered to Sandra, 'Good thing they didn't say encore!'

I remember the day my parents told me we were going to live on the circus. I was so exited. I was only 3 but I loved the circus. My parents used to be in the circus but then they got married and gave up the circus. But whenever the circus comes to town My parents were in it. So when they got the offer to go in the moving circus the accepted it. I was little so it was easy for me to learn how to tame a elephant or to walk on a rope 50 feet in air with no harness.               My first show was amazing. I'll admit that I was a little scared. OK maybe a lot but I LOVED IT. That day I decided that I was never going to leave the circus. Now that I'm 12 I'm having second thoughts.              I woke up and had my breakfast. Today was Friday the 13. Every Friday the 13 we have cupcakes for breakfast, lunch, and dinner. I chose a chocolate cupcake and started eating it.              I was tired of the circus. Moving every single day could get boring. As I sat in my favorite seat my mom joined me. This was my chance.            'Mom do you ever get bored of the circus?' I asked.             ' Sometimes. But I wait.' She replays.             ' Wait for what?'              ' I wait in till I get a great spot in the circus. I practice in till the manger notice how much better I got and gives me a new spot in the show. Maybe that's what you need.' She replays helping herself to a third cupcake.             ' How did' I say, my jaw hanging wide open.             ' How did I know? A mother knows everything.' And with that she leaves the pie car.             All day long I think about what my mom said. When I practice I try something new. Ins-tide of  juggling I ask one of the clowns if I can borrow their unicycles. They give it to me. I find a nice area with a soft landing. Then I start practicing.             Five weeks later when I'm on my unicycle the manger comes and talks me. He gives me a new place in the show.             ' The clowns say you're good. I hope they're right.'' And he walks away.                              That night at the show I lead the elephants out of their tents. On my unicycle. Blindfolded. I tame the elephants into doing tricks with nothing but my hand. It's nice not being able to see because sometimes the crowd mess you up. When I'm down with my act the crowd goes wild.             That night I don't feel like I hate the circus. I love it even more than ever. I realized that the circus isn't about tricks or clowns. It's about trying new things and loving it. For you it might be sports or a new food. For me it's the circus. Like my mom said you have to wait.

Then I ate and we left for the circus.When we got there I bid farewell and told her to come to the show on Saturday.As she left I met a silly clown named Aldo and we quickly became friends.               While we were talking the ringmaster called for everyone to gather round and meet our newest    (drum roll please) PEANUT BOY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! After he said that, he called me up.As I went up everyone cheered and clapped for me. Then he asked who would like to show me around and help me with any questions. Immediately Aldo raised his hand. The ringmaster said 'How about you Aldo.' Aldo came over and said  ' Come on, Let's go!'                 Day by day Aldo helped me around and introduced me to people.By the Saturday I had made many more friends.That night was the show tons and tons of people were there.Finally the acts began. First , all the clowns came out and did funny things like throwing pies at each other.But I didn't see parts because like everyone wanted peanuts. When I spotted Aldo he looked like he was having a good time.Then I heard a Familiar voice saying ' Peanut boy, over here!'I turned around and guess who I saw, MY MOM! I went over to her and gave her a hug and said 'I missed you' I told about my week  and Aldo. She said 'Sounds like fun'.                    When the show was over I Introduced my mom to Aldo. Then asked if I'm going to stay in the circus. I said 'Even though I had so much fun, I think I want to be with my family'.He said 'Okay'.                    Right as we were about to leave Aldo came after me with a big box. I asked him what it was he said it was a gift for me. I opened it and found a clown makeup kit and a bag of the mysterious marshmallow circus peanuts. I said goodbye and thanks and left. I told my mom ' That  was one of the funnest weeks EVER!'                :)

Life of the Circus                Gritting and daring I looked down hoping this moment would never come. I was 100 feet up in the cold night air preparing for what was about to happen. I'm the clown in Rockie Top  Circus. 'I can't believe that my boss wants me to jump onto  a elephant'! I screamed to myself. Then the announcer announced 'ladies and gentlemen, boys and girls of all ages, please welcome Tairan Smith' he said in a deep voice.             'Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaahhhhhhh SLAP!' as I belly flopped onto the rock hard back of the elephant. The show was started! After the show, I was wiped out. We eat at a pie car. ' I'm sick of this job..............I got it! TomorrowI'll run away!            It was cold that morning but I was ready. I set off at 2:15 to start a new life. I was in Idaho and I traveled on foot all the way to California. It took me 4 years to get there. When I got there I saw a poster that said' Rockie Top Circus going out of business IN NEED OF CLOWN'. I thought about all of my friends and sat there for a long time. Finally I decided that there is no place like home. Hi my name is Bella Castini and I am going to tell you what it is like to be in the circus. For example what I have to do in the morning, in the afternoon, and at night. After you read this I hope you will won't to see one of our shows some day.                       First, I I am very busy in the morning. At 7:00 A.M. I get dressed and go out to the pie car for breakfast. We have pancakes and bacon. It is delicious. After I eat we have to set up tents and lights for tonights show. 9:00 A.M. is schooltime. Then I walk to the schoolhouse. The schoolhouse is the same as every school they have computers, tests, and report cards. A lot of the people in the circus are from all around the world ,so many of my classmates speak different languages. When we travel around the world thats when we do geography lessons.                           Next, I have to do tons of jobs in the afternoon to get ready for the show tonight. At 3:00 P.M. school is out. After school I played with the clowns unicycles and juggling balss. It was really fun. 3:30 P.M. is chore time, so I start with the horses. I have to feed, water, and groom the horses. Then I have to start my act. I am leaping off a trampoline and landing on the horse's back. It takes a lot of balance and concentraction. Other kids practice juggling and acrobatics. The trainers are working with baby leopards, elephants,lions, and chimpanzees.                               Last, the end of the night is the best part. At 6:30 P.M. we go to the pie car to eat dinner. Circus performers do not eat much befor the show. The circus does ten shows a week, plus a manitee ( a afternoon show) on Wedensday, two on Saturday, and two on Sunday. The show was really fun and everybody enjoyed it. I did my act and did it. It felt amazing! The show was over and everbody is so tired. We walk back to the trailor. In bed I thought when I growup will I still be in the circus?                                   In Conclusion, I hope I will see you some day performing in the circus. The circus is worth being hard because at the end of the night you are very happy that you are in the circus having fun with friends and family.

The circus is all sorts of fun.  You can play games, get your pictures taken, and much more.  If you ask me the circus is really cool.  The bad thing about being in the circus is that you never get to call a place home.  Also you never get to see your family unless they are in the circus with you.                                                             Life in the circus is hard work if you ask me.  I get to see many people which is fun though.  I get to be an acrobat with my parents.  People always ask me for my autograph.  It is amazing to have people ask you for your autograph because it means people really enjoy you.  I love all my fans, but i don't get to autograph everyone oft them because some times their parents think it's late and then they have to leave.  Other people leave because they don't want to wait in the really long lines.  That is what it is like to have all the fans go crazy for you.                                                                                                The disadvantage of being in the circus is that you never really have a place to call home.  I have a home in Mighigan but it is not very big compared to what i am used to.  It only has five bedrooms.  I have three and my parents have two.  One of my bedrooms is used for my bed and clothes from when i was little and not in the circus.  One of them is used for my circus awards.  I put them in there when we do come home but i usally don't have that much.  The other room is used for my circus clothes that don't fit me anymore.                                                                                                 The hard work I put into the circus is fantastic is what all my fans say.  I do miss my grandma and grandpa and all my other family alot though.  When i have shows in Mighigan they will come and see me.  That's why I love it when we have shows in Mighigan.  Also when we have shows in Virginia my aunt ans uncle come and watch because that is where they live.                                                                                                                                  When we are on our break i play with lego's.  One time I built a mansion because my fans know that i locve lego's and they bring me a bunch.  One time a little girl brought me ten boxes of different lego's.  When i get double of something besides lego's I donate them to a charity in Michigan.  When I do performances at local charities when I am in one state the kids go crazy.  Sometimes I got to an orphanage when I am close to one a do gymnastics in the air on a trampoline.                                                                      I have to live in a trailor which stinks.  The good thing is that they are huge.  I have my own bedroom with a queen size bed in it.  I don't have a closet though.  My parents get the closet.  I don't think that is very fare because I have more clothes then they do.                                                             In conclusion the circus life is pretty cool.  There are some ups.  There are also some downs.  An up is that it is really fun getting to go from state to state.  The down is that you barely ever get to see your family.  Now you know what it is like being in the circus.

For those who say or think that being a circus performer is fun and easy, I have one thing to say to you people, and that is YOU ARE WRONG! The circus life is actually pretty hard. There are many things that you are possibly unaware of in the circus business. Downsides are very common and so are upsides, but there can be more of either to different people though.             There are quite a few hardships for circus performers but I'm only going to tell you some of them. First off one of my most deal-able hardships is how tiring the show is. Our circus does 14 shows a week, one morning show and afternoon show every day! Another hardship is that I have to do almost all the cleaning and chores! But the worst part is I am the animal trainer, so I have to clean up after, groom, take care of, bath, and feed the animals! One of the most hardest hardships is that I cannot visit my family because of my very busy schedule and I cannot visit my friends either! So being a circus performer has a lot of downsides.             Circus performing isn't all bad though. It has its own upsides! Such as, getting to travel the world! I get to see many things around the world! Once I saw the Eiffel Tower, The Statue Of Liberty, and The White House! You also get to see the audience compliment you and see them get 'transported to another world'! I also get to learn new things and tricks as I rehearse and practice. And I do love seeing the children's happy faces once they go to our circus! We also get to eat food that is paid for by the circus. Even with many downsides the circus life is still pretty good!             Another thing I forgot to mention was the profits! I am also the 'treasurer' of the circus. I'm not even sure if circuses are even supposed to have one, but anyways I'm in charge of the profits. And that is hard work! I have to pay everyone depending on how many people paid and gave feedback. I also have to use the money and my FREE time to buy new equipment if we want new equipment or if we need to replace broken equipment. I also have to pay for accidents, candy, one-time-use kind of things, and souvenirs, but I don't have to pay the bills!   That's the owner's problem.             So in the end, circus life to me is exhausting, but it is still a pretty good life. So if I were to recommend being a circus performer I would say it depends on if you are a good acrobatic, but this job does pay a lot!

I was practicing my acrobatics when I was called to the back of the circus.  Apparently everybody else was too.  Our boss told us that instead of performing at a regular show, we would be competing with other circuses.  The first place circus would be known all over the world.  Us people of Big Top Circus were excited.  Our boss also said that only one person would be annonced the best out of all the circuses.  They would be famous all over the world too.  Now we were really excited.  I wasn't really sure if I would get to be the best.  I knew my friend, Drew, should get it.  She was the best trapeze artist out of the whole circus.  The competition was on Saturday, August 21.  That was only a week from today.  I really needed to practice my acrobatics.         It was Wednesday, August 18.  Only two days left to practice.  I almost broke my ankle trying to land back down after doing my last acrobatic practice yesterday.  It was a good thing I didn't.  Then I wouldn't be able to participate in the competition.  I was doing a really cool routine high in the air with Drew.  I would spin and turn and twirl on a rope and then Drew would come down on her trapeze and get me.  I would fly in the air with Drew, let go of her and do a backflip, and then land clean on my feet.  It was a hard routine.         It was now the day of the competition.  I couldn't wait.  Our circus would be judged last.  We had to perform exellent to impress the judges.  It was finally for our circus to go on.  Drew's and I routine would be going last. We really had to impress the judges.  Maybe Drew would get to be the best performer.  If it wasn't me, it should be her.  It was now our turn.  I was nervous and so was Drew.  She was actually shaking.  I walked over to my rope and started spinning and turning.  Drew then came down on her trapeze and I grabbed her legs and flew with her.  Then I let go of her legs, did a backflip, and landed clean on my feet.          I hoped the routine looked great.  It was time to give out the awards.  So far we haven't been called and they were now going to announce who got first place....'And the circus who got first place is..... BIG TOP CIRCUS!'  I was so surprised I started crying a little bit.  Now they were going to announce the best performer.  'And the best performer is....ZOIE BAEZA!'  Now I really started crying.  I was now so shocked ans surprised that I got it.  I would be famous all around the world even if I died right now.  A week later we were already traveling all aroung the world and many people wanted my autograph at the same time.  The Big Top Circus was now a world wide circus, and so was I.

Today is your first day at the circus. You get the job to be an acrobat. You have to be the one to hang on the bars and ropes. You are very afraid of hights, but you have to do it anyway. So you climb up on the ladder and get on the rope. After a few minutes people start to notice you are hanging on a rope. A few people walk by and clap for you and tell you to do a trick. You don't know what to do so you put one foot on the rope and the other in the air. Then you do the same thing with your arms. You balance for about 8 minutes with one foot and one arm in the air and one foot and arm on the rope. People clap and tell you to come back tomorrow. After that day was over you walk home and go to bed after a long day of hard work.   The next day you go to the circus to be an acrobat, but then your boss says you ar going to be a juggler instead. he told me he wanted me to learn to do everything so then I could do different things each day. So before people started showing up I practiced. I didn't notice for a few minutes but out of the corner of my eye two people were watching me practice. They started telling me to juggle bananas, so they gave me some and told me to try. I tried and I was actually really good at it. i could also do jumping jacks while I juggled.       After a couple of days I wsa getting tired of doing acrobat and juggling so I asked if I could try tightrope walking. My boss said of course. So i got up on the tightropoe and tried balancing. I could balance pretty well so i tried a trick. I did a flip and a back flip. People were so amazed. everyone was smiling and it made me smile.       The two days after it was Saturday. It was my day off. I spent the whole day practicing. I loved being at the circus. I couldn't wait till Monday so I made my own circus at my house. I made myself look like a clown. I juggled, did acrobats, and did tightrope walking.

A day at the circus                            The day had come, I was so exited, I jumped out of bed got my cloths on and ran down stairs. I ate my cereal and got in the car. Sadly my parents were not in the car. I ran inside and dragged them into the car. We were on our way to the circus. I was so exited all I said to my parents was, 'are we there yet' about one thousand times. I finally got bored of saying that, so I just sat there quietly.                             Then in the horizon I saw a tent, at first I thought it was just some campers but as I got closer and closer I realized that we were finally here. I was so exited that I couldn't speak. we found a parking spot as quickly as we could. I jumped out of the car and ran inside. It was every thing I dreamed it would be but better. On one side there was the snack shop and on the other there were performers giving out signatures. i ran in the doors there they were our own reserved seats. Once I sat down the lights turned off.                              A small man came out he said,' welcome to the Circus Ole, we hope you have the best night of your lives.' As soon as he finished He turned taller and taller. Then something came out of the sky it was a mini plane, it was awesome. Then acrobats came fling out then landed on a trampoline were they started doing all of these cool moves. Out of no were these performers swinging on these glow in the dark ropes. The strangest thing happened, a elephant was riding on rollerskates.                              Next balloons started falling out of the sky and then got real quite. A mime was stacking chairs in an odd way then I couldn't believe it, he started climbing them. I new he was going to fall at the very top he started staking more and more, he was insane. I am very excited for today's show. The circus that I am in is called 'The Best Circus On Earth' and we are performing in California. I have not been to California, even though I travel all over the world. The circus will be here all week so I get to perform 10 times! One show on weekdays, but Wednesday there are two shows and two shows on the weekends.       After I ate breakfast, I went to the school room. The school room is like any other regular school only, it travels with the circus. School is over at 3:00. We have 6 hours of school because we need to train. Besides performing, my favorite part of the day is the after school break. I usually play with the clowns and they teach me how to juggle. After my break, my friend and I feed the horses. Today, I am working on leaping onto horses, and then jumping off of it. My friends are working on juggling and acrobatics. Other acts are training their lions, elephants, and monkeys.       It is 6:30, dinner time is finally here. My family and I go to the pie car to eat, but we can't eat too much because of the show. Now it is time for the show! When it is time for my act,  I pull it off perfectly. I love seeing the crowd get excited and enjoy the show. The show is over at 10:30 and I am very tired. Even though I am tired, I can't wait for the next day so I can perform again.       Being a circus performer is lots of fun. I love being around all the circus members and I love to perform. I would be happy if I could return home to New York but as long as I can be around my family doing what I love I would be happy.
